comment: Dr. Pelloquin passed away in August 2009
Great class.

Wow, one of the best professors ever...his tests apply the "what do you know" rather than "can you get the answer right" type questions.  Impossible tests, no, very difficult? Absolutely.  VERY MATH ORIENTED...DO NOT TAKE IF YOU ARE NOT GOOD AT MATH!  He is a Physical Chemist, meaning that his 111 and 112 classes will be more math application.
Does not teach material very well at all. Easy grader, but I didn't learn a single thing. Test were incomprehensible and extremely difficult. Stay away from this teacher, take anyone else!
Really easy grader. Not very good at explaining material in my opinion.

This was a 3 weekend course on Hermeneutics. There was A LOT of reading, and could be really overwhelming at times, but Jerry teaches well and respects everyone's opinions and interpretations of the subject matter. The class felt more like a club or secret society that you chose to be a part of rather than a mandatory class for credits.

This was a one weekend one credit class called Self Talk. It was very interesting and inspirational. For about 10 of the 16 hours allotted for the class, we were advised to go away, alone, without music or people or social media, and just be with ourselves, listening to our self talk. Though it sounds boring or weird, it was very revealing.

The information is very dense in this class, however Jerry made it interesting and gave great lectures.  Some people are intimidated by him, therefore don't engage, however you will learn so much from him.  He will challenge you and really make you think.  If you do all of the work it's easy to get a good grade in his class.

Great teacher! This is a tough class but Jerry makes it easier to get through the subject matter and is very understanding. I would highly recommend taking this class from Jerry if you need to get it done.

Fantastic teacher. He has an unorthodox teaching style which is hard for some students. That's why his classes are effective. If your plan is to take the easiest classes possible to prepare for a future in flipping burgers an Burger King do not take him. If you care about your education, take him and be prepared to think, argue, and grow.

Being a TA for one of Jerry's classes is really fun and interesting. Being able to help students and support their learning was very gratifying. Grading students papers and tests was the hardest but also the most fulfilling part of being an assistant. If Jerry asks you to be a TA in one of his classes I suggest taking advantage of the opportunity.

Jerry is still my favorite professor. I took COMM 160 first semester as a freshman and COMM 131 over the summer.  He may confuse you because he will not talk down to you. If you ask a question he can ask you two more that will lead you down a path of incredible intellectual discovery.

His class was a disaster. Very unorganized and he gives no direction on the papers. SO much reading and you never know what he is going to test you on and they are just plain hard. The service learning and group project is a NIGHTMARE!! He's an awesome person, but the class is structured very poorly. YOU'VE BEEN WARNED.
Although there is quite a bit of required reading in this class, it was outstanding and full of critical thinking and interaction. Jerry is a pleasure to learn from and with.

Yes, Jerry has a different style of teaching, but even though I was intimidated at first, I learned to appreciate him.   He gives great lectures and  there is a lot of reading, but if you put the work into class you will be fine.  I  learned so much about listening and myself.  Highly recommended class! He has a great sense of humor too!
Jerry is an outstanding professor.  It's hard at first, but once you hit the learning curve it all falls into place.

Jerry is wonderful. Listening is a hard class but it is quite possibly the most important class that I have taken to date. The information you will learn in this class will give you more insight and skills in communication and listening than you might have ever anticipated. All of the books are online which is awesome, save trees save money!

Overall, it was a very confusing class. He didn't redo the syllabus so all the dates were off and even the TA's didn't know when things were due. My class was all service learning based and quiz based. Be prepared to fail every quiz. Even the head TA said he got a C average in quizzes. Not helpful at all.

If you don't want to take communication study seriously, DO NOT TAKE HIS CLASSES. But, if you do take his classes seriously, he will give you more value than any other professor. I've taken many of his classes and I've learned a lot about myself and the beliefs I have that lead me to communicate the way I do. You will do a lot of introspection!

I thought Jerry was a great teacher!  He really peaked my interest in the subject.  I would definitely take another class from him.  His class does take work.  There is a lot of reading and writing, so if you want a class that doesn't take a lot of time this is not your class.
Jerry is an amazing instructor, this class won't just give you the credits you need to graduate, it will give you tools you need to LIVE.

Jerry is a nice guy but I did not enjoy this class. The material is really ambiguous, the TA's do all the grading(they are not helpful), Jerry is not very helpful if you are confused. The tests are hard. There is a ton of readying- he provides, you do not buy a textbook.

This class may be a 100 level class but the work load is that of a 300 level class. Do not take this class unless your willing to actually do your work. He is such an incredible teacher and is so smart, he makes you think about everything, dont let others fool you because they probably didn't do their work. This class is GREAT!,he is GREAT!

I took this class from Jerry in 2008.  I found him to be very condescending and unable to adequately respond to answers asked by students.  Once a couple of students were laughing at a comment another student made and he became enraged and snapped at them.  He is too aggressive and just doesn't seem stable at all.  Should not be a professor.
Very reading and labor intensive but an amazing professor.  Articulate what you don't understand and you'll do great.  Loved this!

GREAT teacher. Had a weekend workshop with him & was not expecting the outcome. Very valuable information. If you want to think critically, take any of his classes. He is EXTREMELY intelligent. Wish I had taken more courses throughout my career with him.

I've never had to write a review, but he is the most unfocused, unhelpful, and unclear professor I have ever had. His class is a joke that he leaves to his TAs to take care of. When he actually lectures he will ask questions and stare at you to make you feel guilty and uncomfortable. You will not learn anything. Save your money and DO NOT take him!

Jerry is an awesome teacher! Honestly this class is pretty hard to understand, but if you pay attention in your discussion groups and skim the readings during quizzes you can pass easily. His TA's do all the grading so make your essays sound smart. And he lets you use a blue book on midterm and final!!! Easy A or B if you ask me
Like anything worthwhile this class is very demanding. If you really want to be a bettet communicator Jerry will take you there.Stay plugged in and participate and you will grow as a person.

Jerry is a GREAT teacher - but he's not for everyone. If you participate and you DO the work, you'll be fine. Don't take this class if you're just trying to get easy credits, take this class because you care about the topic and you want to LEARN! The people complaining are the ones that just wanted to have everything spelled out for them.

While all the comments about him assigning work not pertaining to the class is true, Jerry is one of the smartest professors I've had in college.  This guy will get you to think critically and teach you what college learning should be.  Just don't expect to be spoon-fed info and you'll be fine.

Jerry is an awesome teacher! If you put in some effort and apply critical thinking skills, you'll pass. He's not a professor that will hand you all the information you need on a silver platter, but if you're in college, you should be capable of figuring things out on your own. He wants his students to actually learn something!

Ok this class is a complete joke.  It makes no sense and has no practical use in the real world. Jerry just assigns a ton of reading with no background to the material. the good news is that he does no grading and makes his TAs do all the work. avoid at all costs. I spent all semester asking why do i even show up anymore

You'd think that a listening class in the comm dept would be a really great, educational experience. As long as this teacher is in charge, that will never happen. Students are idiots, listening is something way out there, and I never understand a word he says. He does love to talk though. I should have taken something else from someone else.

Don't let the syllabus overwhelm you. This class is all about effort. If you do your very best and it's obvious, you will get an A. Plus there are alternatives to taking the final and you get to use a blue book full of notes on the midterm. The only way you can fail this class is by not caring, not turning in your homework and being overall lazy.

If you need to be spoon fed to learn don't take Jerry's class. If you want to be a much better communicator hang on, keep up with the dance, and ask real questions. If you stay plugged in he will help you. Great class for overcoming stage fright.

If you genuinely try to follow jerry, and attempt to understand and engage in discussion, you will do fine in his class.  he is very passionate, and yes, he does lose sight sometimes that the students aren't on the same intellectual page, but ask him to clarify, and he is nothing but smiles and help.  really nice guy, too.

does not explain information well, treats the 100 level course like a 300 level course, gives brief info then leaves it up to you to read and figure out what he is saying. will not directly answer questions. doesn't update gradebook. does however allow to change due dates

This man might take the cake for one of the worst professors I've had. It's as if his purpose is to make every person in the classroom (TAs included) extremely uncomfortable. On occasion, I've watched him listen to someone's question and then ignore it as if it had never been asked because he feels it's too stupid to answer.

I have always hated communications but taking this class with Jerry made it almost unbearable.  He embarrasses students and requires so much work to be done I am amazed he is still employed with Boise State.  Nobody seems to like him.  This semester we are required to do multiple journal entries, quizzes, midterm, final, 3 presentations and a paper

He gives homework everyday over Bb due dates are hard to follow rambles on over subjects not involved over test. TA does all the grading, get another professor at all cost just a horrible horrible professor.

The best professor I've ever had. Very, very intellectual. Material taught in an easy-to-understand way that makes you think. Truly a wonderful professor once you understand YOU are responsible for your learning.
Terrible class. Professor rambles on and on about irrelevant things the entire class. TA does most if not all of his work for him. Do not take a class that he teaches.

So I was rather skeptical about taking this class (listening) after reading these other comments, but now i really should gone with my gut instinct and not taken it.this is the most unstructured god awful class ever. jerry is very smart but im not sure with what. the class is all over the place. jerry has no clue how to teach.the material is useles

Jerry is one of the most difficult professors to understand that I've ever had, and I'm a senior. However, with the use of his TA's and one-on-one meetings, one can wade through the immense amount of material required and do well in the class. He is definitely intellect, and with that sometimes he is difficult to understand highly recommend him tho

Way too much busy work for this class.  I would forget what was due each class.  He's a nice guy, but he makes the class difficult.  His TA really does do all the grading.  I would highly recommend taking this class from someone else!

I honestly have to say this is the worst professor I have ever had. Not because it is a difficult class for an intro class, but because this teacher doesn't accept emails or phone calls and his TA will usually ignore those so its very hard to get a hold of someone. The class structure is very unorganized, he doesn't know how to even use bb.

Jerry is a wonderful teacher, full of knowledge, wit and wisdom. He is a true intellect which I think is hard for younger students to wrap their head around.He expresses that he is always learning from his students as they learn from him. If your looking for a true learning experience take his classes.

Jerry was a great guy but the class is really HARD. Everything he said went in one ear and out the other. Very hard to grasp what he is saying. His TA did all the grading for him. Hint: get along with the TA ;)
He is a super nice guy you just have to get to know him.

Being a senior about to graduate now, I would have to say he was the worst teacher I have ever had. He had his TA grade everything for him, even the paper worth a lot of your grade and she had only taken the class the semester before. He was also flirty and it was disturbing. Would not recommend him for a teacher.

Jerry's confusing and pointless lectures along with the lack of a textbook make it impossible to grasp the subject. His TAs do everything for him & he won't let you see what you did wrong on tests & quizzes. Service Learning was overly difficult- the ANA was disorganized & didn't communicate well & Jerry held us responsible for it.

Jerry is a rather hard proff and He may be a little scattered because communication is a rather hard topic to keep on one track. being discussed the train. He is a very good professor if you are in his class to learn. If you plan on slacking then you might want a professor who doesn?t care.I highly recomend Jerry for this class as well as lis 131!

Unless you enjoy hours of mindless, stupid, petty assignments (2-4/week) STAY AWAY! He doesn't open the necessary documents on BB in a timely manner so you're constantly scrambling to submit stuff on time.  He's confusing, incredibly rude if you disagree with his abstract thinking, & will call you out & demoralize you in front of the entire class.

Enjoys confusing students, is very stubborn on what he thinks. Seems to have a short temper, and doesn't make sense in his argument. Using Bb in all the wrong ways, making it almost impossible to know what to expect in class, wastes your time searching for things. All he cares about is service learning, unless your doing that, avoid him.

Scatters ALL assignments across BB, doesn't mention them before or after they're due, it's up to YOU to find the work, do the research and turn it in on time. Class time is 2 hours a week of abstract discussions that leave you more confused than when you entered. He is very intelligent and helpful on the rare occasions he can be steered on subject.

Very unorganized, unclear, total hippy. Class is a free for all. Everyone just writes in their journal and listens to his nonsense. He brought in a guest and they like hugged the whole time - it was weird! I quit going and retook from Mary Most - WAY BETTER TEACHER!

He makes a big deal about coming to class but it's never anything important and it's always boring. He posts EVERYTHING on Bb so its hard to find stuff and he never lets you know when things are due. The assignments are mostly busy work and pretty easy to B.S. but there's a lot of it. Avoid him if you can.

Jerry really is a great teacher! He can be hard to wrap your mind, sometimes - but if you stick in there, it will all be worth it. It is not a typical 100 level class. Jerry makes you think, and really develop your own opinion. I would highly recommend this class to anyone who is willing to think and take a step outside of their box!

If you're looking to skate through a one-hundred level class, this is not the one.  The professor is a complete idiot, he's rude, and shouldn't be teaching entry-level students.  He obviously is being forced to by upper mgmt and makes the students pay for it.  He is probably one the biggest disappointments concerning BSU

Group work was helpful and usually pretty fun but the class discussions were always off topic and generally didn't relate to what we were learning about at all. Do your reading, go to class and participate in the group work to get a good grade. If you don't, you're screwed.
A lot of busy work, but he was fun once you got to know him. Importance on group work.

I'm going to go out on a limb here and say that this professor is the worst on campus. He is unrealistic, hypocritcal and he's very ignorant.  You should try and avoid him at all cost.  Prepare for a lot of BS and confusing/useless theories and lectures!  Good luck if you're the poor soul that has to endure this professor.

I loathed going to this class. The readings we did were practically incomprehensible and lecture was just a random string of people talking about their opinions. I felt this class was useless. I hated his teaching style, most everything that you had to do was pointless, and I learned almost nothing.

This is the worst professor I have ever had. He bargained with us one day and promised we wouldn't have to do an assignment. The next week he gave us that assignment, when I spoke up against him he began ignoring me in class. He "loses" assignments if he doesn't like you. He rambles about complete nonsense.  Awful human and teacher

His listening class is a joke. He is unorganized and talks of things that make no sense. He thinks that he is brining interesting info to the class but it always felt he just talked to talk and use big words to purposely confuse the students. The activities were worthless & he has many TA's and they do all of his work. Def. take a different class
His class was horribly orchestrated and he himself is extremely. If you take Comm 101 from him be sure to do service learning--it's 100 pts. and you don't have to take the final. Aced his class!

I really would not recommend his listening class. He uses lots of jargon when he speaks, and makes no sense. The class really has no value to any learning, and his TA's do all of the work. He has about 7 TA's and they are the ones that assign you grading for the class. For a 100 level class, its incredible dubious and lots of work for no payoff.

Jerry is very disorganized, he likes to think this is not true.  His syllabus schedule was hard to understand and due dates are never clear.  He has you do group work and that is never fun. Especially when you have to rely on them for a good grade.  He is very set in his ways and political views and brings that to class. Try a diff. professor!!
too much homework

Most assignments have to be posted on blackboard, which Jerry doesn't even know how to use half the time.  Due dates are very confusing and he never reminds you when you have some upcoming due date for a paper/assignment.  There is a LOT of work to do for this class, more so than most of the other Comm 101 classes I've heard about.

class is very unorganized and relies too heavily on blackboard. assignments and due dates are extremely vague. jerry is pretty ranty and will get off track easily about government and whatnot. the class is easy but there is a ton of work for a required 101 class and a lot of it is unrelated to communication. many classes were wasted watching movies
Teaches in depth communication skills. Introduces abstract thinking.  Very literate.

Highly theoretical, i.e. don't expect techniques to improve your listening! The class work is not rigorous, but depth and breadth of discusion is impressive. If you engage yourself even a little, Jerry's Listening class and workshops are life changing. A huge plus, Jerry makes himself very available to students for questions and discussions.

I spent two semesters with Jerry. One as a student and one as a TA, both in Listening. The class is fantastic and far more in depth than the title suggests. Jerry is very laid back, but always keeps things interesting. He wonders aloud a lot, but if you stay with him on his meanderings, you WILL learn something. :)
Jerry was a great teacher! I would definitely take him again!

Ok Jerry's class is very difficult, but if you like communications, it's worth it. You can learn a lot, but he makes you work for it. Lots of homework, but most the points are from the exams. I did less than half the assignments through the year and got an A. If you are just trying to ger core classes out of the way get a different teacher.
This class was easy if you do the work. The reading isn't necessary if you use the study guide for the midterm and final. He is laid back, but respectable, kind of a hippie, but appreciates honesty.

this is easily the worst prof I've had, she was no help at all in class and and just makes you read and work straight out of the textbook. despite hours of grinding homework and studying, I still didn't pass. if you find yourself in her class, I hope you're ready to watch youtube tutorials
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: Extremely tough. Her intro Spanish class she taught in ONLY Spanish leaving the students to learn everything outside of class on our own. She also doesn't respond to emails, or post anything online. Very hard class, avoid unless you're already fluent and just want the credit.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: Professor Waldner's class is a great example of really getting into the next level of conversational Spanish with lots of interaction and hands on activities. She really cares about students improving and developing if they want to keep pursuing higher level Spanish classes. She is really professional and always willing to help students noproblem
ratingTags: Respected--Participation matters--Amazing lectures

comment: I had Flor for two different classes and I can honestly say she's been one of my favorite teachers. She truly cares for the students success. You will walk out of her class having learned something. Not just a class where you memorize and forget after. Wouldn't have had much luck abroad without her help with the language.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Gives good feedback--Respected

comment: I don't agree with any of the negative ratings. Flor is a passionate, kind, fair and an enthusiastic teacher. I think the problem is that some students are used to high school teachers catering for them but this is college. Quiz/tests are just like the practice handouts. Wrong to blame Flor if you lack the prior knowledge that is expected in 102.

I had her for Span102 and my Spanish actually regressed. She speaks too fast, wasn't prepared, insisted we participate but then if you gave the wrong answer moves on to the next student without explanation.  Final is way different than chapter tests.  Her English is terrible.  If you're struggling, her solution is tutoring.  Doesn't answer e-mails.

I think Flor is getting a bad rap on this site.  She's fair, enthusiastic, professional, tough, doesn't put up with BS, and doesn't want to hear your excuses.  She wants you to participate.  Will help if you're having trouble.  It's a tough class that requires work.  You can't coast through for an easy grade.  Finally, best trasero at BSU.

Flor Waldner is from Columbia. So, she has an accent and had to learn English as a second language. Therefore, her lectures can be a little rough. Other than that, she is a wonderful woman. Very compassionate, wants to help you learn. She usually explains exactly what will be on the exams, which is very helpful. I would definitely recommend her!

Zero willingness to work with differing schedules. If in the service, may try to not comply with law regarding drill and missed class. A guardian of the 'A'; expect to jump through many hoops to obtain it. Excessive workload for a 100-level class; I have 400-level classes that don't require as much outside of class "busy work". Grueling experience.

Make sure you can understand spoken Spanish before you take her class, because she talks fast (but enunciates well). I found it relatively easy to get an A in her class, as long as you do the work and know your stuff going in (I'm not a native speaker). She makes it clear what she wants, but she makes it clear in Spanish.

I don't understand the negative reviews. She was a very enthusiastic, interested, and caring professor. She cared greatly about the success of her class in learning advanced Spanish. Beware, however, that she grades rather harshly and will nitpick your mistakes. I just barely got an A and I worked my tail off for it. All in all, would take again.

Flor is a hard grader but very unspecific about what she wants. She has the idea that you "should know" by the time you get to 303. It makes it next to impossible to get an A unless you are a native speaker and even then it isn't easy. Easily the worst Spanish professor at Boise State.

Flor is very nice and if you have questions she will try to answer them. However, she will not speak in English so if you have a question expect an answer in Spanish. She is a really tough grader. I did not like her teaching style very much, and she seems pretty unprepared for classes.

This was the worst professor I have ever had. I took her medical terminology class and her 303 class, was never given a study guide, her tests were always different and very rarely we would get tested on what we learned. She grades really tough and was not helpful. If you can, DO NOT TAKE ANY OF HER CLASSES. She's an awful professor.

Flor was nice, but seemed to make up her class work on the spot. Everything seemed thrown together and nothing is really explained. She will throw homework at you last minute, so if you like to live by the syllabus don't take her. She seems like someone I'd enjoy more out of the classroom.

Not a nice person, although she acts like it on a superficial level. Treats students like they are in junior high and openly humiliates them on a whim. Her English should be a lot better if she wants to teach at a university level.

Flor was... interesting. A harsh grader to say the least. She was really nice, and sometimes helpful, but a lot of the times her grading was just too intense. Participate! You will get a low grade if you do not.
I love Flor as a person but hate her as a teacher. She is a harsh grader and she is terrible at explaining what she expects.

Flor was by no means an easy teacher, but if you had questions or needed clarification you could always ask and she would be helpful. I've always struggled with learning a new language and she understood that I came and tried my best. She understands not everyone is at the same level!

Terrible. I have a bachelors degree from this university and have never encountered such a useless professor. I can see how she would be a good choice for upper division but isn't suited for a lower division class. There were times that she didn't seem to understand the questions asked by students. Select a different professor!

Flor is very confusing at times. When you have a question she doesn't clearly answers it. She really cares about her class, but her grading is ridiculous. Apparently by the end of the 3rd semester of Spanish we have to be fluent. I worked VERY hard to get a B in this class.
Very difficult to understand when teaching in Spanish. From Columbia, Teaches only in Spanish.  Hard to follow along.  Was in over my head-had to switch classes just to ensure I wing to pass.

Generally nice. Will help you improve your Spanish. She was not always fair in the class I took from her. She and I talked about letting me use the ebook version of the text to save $ but then she threatened to take my computer away (yeah, no). Went off on a couple kids one day and threatened to call security to escort them out just for talking.

Flor was fantastic! She is a great teacher, and really cares that you are understanding the topics she is teaching.  The whole class is in Spanish, so be prepared to listen REALLY well. Tests are VERY easy, and as long as you pay attention in class and have decent notes, you will pass the tests.
Flor is really nice, this class was tough though.

Awesome teacher, she's the best language teacher on campus. Tough grader though, not sure if she realizes we're not fluent yet. I'm aking her for 102 now, and I'll take her for two more additonal classes as well. Nice Colombian booty, too ;)

She really is a nice lady, but she is such a tough grader! The participation and presentation grading is ridiculous. I didn't miss a single class and participated actively and only got 85 out of 100...she told the class the last week it was impossible to get more than 90...wtf? Also, she doesn't speak very good eng, so she is hard to understand.

She's a fun and involved teacher, but capricious in her grading. Her assignment expectations are definitely NOT made clear and she is generally unwilling to communicate in English. Her office hours are by appt - that is to say, non-existent - because she's seldom in her office, never returns phone calls, and is slow to respond to emails.

Pretty intense teacher, and very good.  Had a hard time getting used to her accent (native speaker).  She's very enthusiastic, fair, and kind.  Grades low on participation so speak up.  Tests are book based and passable.  I learned a lot and really liked Flor.  Would take her again.  Highly recommended.  Oh yeah, great outfits...
Flor is a fantastic teacher that puts everything she has into the class but also expects the same from you. Not an easy class but you will definitely learn Spanish from her.

Senora Waldner was an amazing Spanish teacher! It kind of stinks that you have to go to class 4 days a week, but she makes it worth it and keeps it fun, exciting and interesting! She is VERY helpful and understanding. If you miss a day she won't be mad, and I think if you tell her in advance she may not count it. Great teacher!! Don't pass her up!
Flor Maria Waldner is the type of prof that will treat everyone fairly. She is very good at teaching Spanish and I will be taking it from her next semester as well.
Rosemary was an excellent instructor! She always took the time to explain rationale to the students and was patient. You do need to know your stuff going into class though.
She is willing to help students at any time and is great at accepting questions. I have never seen her make someone feel unappreciated or stupid. Overall, Rosemary is a wonderful professor!
Excellent professor. Very knowledgeable about the subject matter.

This class was required for the program and the material was interesting, but not in the manner in which it was delivered.  She is a very dry in her delivery of material.  She always looks like she is upset or annoyed with people - hard person to read.
Lectures are a bit boring to sit through, but if you study and read your books, you can do okay.

He is a no B.S. professor who will tell you like it is. He has real world experience and you will learn a lot from him. If you show up for class, do the weekly extra credit, study the easy weekly assignments, write your papers COBE style (content really doesn't matter), and don't get nervous on presentations,you'll get an A without much difficulty.

I took professor Ware for the 8 week course he is very abrupt, obnoxious, hard, and will tell you like it is, if you get offended easily don't take him. I showed up to class everyday participated and even got an F on a paper and still ended up with a B. Mandatory attendance, 2 papers 2 presentations, participation and that's it he is intimidating.

I took him for Leadership Skills the first 8 weeks of this current semester.  He is HARD, unfair at times, and ready for retirement.  However, I learned SO MUCH from this class and him.  Expect to be treated unfairly, ridiculed, and demanded too much from...but it you can pull off the extra credit papers every week, an A possible.

Jim Ware is a very direct professor. I enjoyed his class very much because he is straight forward and to the point. He has many stories from his life in business and often brings treats. I took his 8 week class which was intense, but way worth it. He makes you think on your feet. I got an A with work as a team leader. I learned a lot. Take him.

This adjunct prof is incredibly ambiguous and vague in his guidelines and instructions for assignments, but then will grade you extremely harshly if you don't meet his mystery criteria.  A lot of the class is ultimately guessing what he wants and crossing your fingers.  He refuses to help you AT ALL.  Do not take this class from Jim Ware.

horrible teacher. she read from her slides when lecturing, and the home work was crazy. for one chapter she would have you answer 30 to 80 questions.half the class was in class work. Don't take this class with her.

I felt like it was an easy class. Quizes actually are full-blown exams. They don't have much weight on your grade, but if you do terrible on all it will drop you one letter grade. Quiz is 100% out of the book, nothing from lecture. Lots of busy work, but easy grade. Just show up and do the work and you will pass with flying colors.

One of the worst prof I have ever had at BSU.  She is totally unprofessional, rude to students, no itinerary, no posted grades, lectures have nothing to do with tests.  Test are between 90-120 questions and she will tell you about a week before the test when it is.  Horrible experience...I would not recommend this class to anyone.
i don't recommend her

There are some aspects of this class that were interesting but overall it was confusing. The exams are all over the book yet there is not one lecture on the book in class, everything is over pharmasim and case studies. It feels like you are taking two classes, it is not cohesive at all. Would not recommend her for this class.

This teacher was extremely hard. 90 questions on the tests and you only have less then an hour to do. and most of the questions are scenarios which is hard. you must attend class, and she doesnt help you at all! i would never recoment this teacher.

While you must attend class in order to recieve a good grade in this class, she makes it so easy to do well if you just come to class. She is just a lady who worked in marketing and is now teaching a class, she is not a teacher and it shows.  She gets terms and definitions mixed up.  You have weekly reading quizzes over the reading material so you have to stay on top of all reading.  She can't handle technology and won't use blackboard to help students because it scares her.

comment: Lectures were alright but very dry; he worked through many example problems. Homework came from MyStatsLab. He gives group quizzes every week, but they were easy.
He is really passionate about teaching.
Mr. Shannon is a great teacher for a difficult subject.
The hardest thing about this class is the subject. From what I hear though he is easier than a lot of other professors.  Be prepared to work though, it is very thick material.

He's a good teacher and knows his stuff.  I think the subject is boring but he at least presents it well.  The homework is very time consuming but if you do it the tests are fairly easy.  Not my favorite teacher ever but I would take another class from him.

Very rigorous class, but a caring and considerate teacher.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Gives good feedback--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: Awful. One work: Suffocating. It's like she tries to control your life. Thinking the only thing you're interested in or have time for is clarinet. I was encouraged many times to take out unnecessary school loans for such a useless degree. Will definitely never study with again.

Dr. Moreau is a competent and difficult teacher that expects high quality of work from her students. She is really a great teacher that will help students that ask. I have a kid and work part time while going to school full time, and I still managed to get an A in her class. If I can, so can you-- Just be there and be ready to learn.

Dr Moreau will give out lots of homework yes but you better be guaranteed that you come out knowing the stuff she taught you. i was upset about the amount at first until i realized i got A's on my tests because i knew it all easy from the homework!

I had this teacher for the first in the series of four music theory classes.  I was very interested in music theory coming in, now I hate it.  She assigns so much homework that it's ridiculous.  Maybe if you have nothing to do but theory homework, you'll be fine, but I doubt it.  I asked her for help once and she told me "Figure it out." Ridiculous

She is an Awesome teacher, By far my favorite one here, she also is my Private lessons teacher so any Clarinet students as well she is one of the best players i have ever heard, truly a treat to have her as a teacher no matter what
She is very helpful, but very serious about having the students do the homework. She wants you to understand what you're learning.I really enjoyed this class, I learned a lot.
no tests, only essays. I basically rewrote his essay questions and BSed everything and got an A. All you need is basic writing skills

Easy A... Just type up something interesting papers are like one page double spaced font size 14 so not very long... he cares a lot about his students and will work with you on anything... by the way no tests only two papers and not even long
Hated this class!! There wasn't a textbook it was a packet with practically no useful information.

Some good things about McNeel.  1.  He really is enthusiastic about history.  That's awesome.  2.  You can tell that the thing he cares most about is that the students actually learn about history, not whether or not they make good automatons.  Props to his teaching style.    One thing I will say is that the text he picked was kinda dry and boring.

dr. mcneel takes an awesome approach to history. there are no tests, only papers on why certain quotes, people, events are important in US history. I have never had a class like this before. Well done Teach.

Rather unorthodox teaching style but easy if you like discussion and concept learning.  Keep up on the readings and be prepared to write your toughts at every class and you'll get an A. No tests - papers are not long. Good teacher - I took him for Ed-Cifs 201 as well and learned a lot.
He is an awesome teacher. He makes the class fun and interesting. You will do well if you do the reading. Lots of writing, but you will learn a lot.

This professor was completely unprofessional, he could not keep track of what week were on so he gave us one assignment 2 weeks late, leaving it due along with another assignment on the last day of class, keep in mind we wrote 3 major papers so 2/3 were due on the last day. He cancelled class 6 times and watched us during his evaluation time.

This was a great class from a great professor.  He really involved the class in meaningful discussions and we learned a lot about philosophy and education practices. I recommend taking this class from him if you can.  Fair grader, not hard if you keep up with the readings.

Great profesor! Made the class fun and interesting. Very young and energetic. Sometimes a little too energetic. A lot of in-class activities with partners. Tests were very straight forward. She is very talkative, but she's fun and outgoing. Her tests aren't "easy" but she's really lenient for grading. I'd recommend her.
I thought Kristing was very professional but kept the class entertaining.  I had her two years ago for Span 101 and now I am in Span 303, 2 years later.
DiBartolo is a terrible professor.  The class itself is easy as long as you study and participate.  She complains a lot and talks about herself constantly.

I don't know what that person is talking about...I thought Kristen was a wonderful professor. I learned more from one semester with her than I did two years in highschool! She is sweet and always willing to help.

She acts like she is 12 and tries too hard to be your friend not your professor.  She likes to talk about herself all the time.  Kind of like an annoying highschool girl.  If you like teachers like that go ahead and try it out.  If you study you will do fine.  I just didn't like her.

If you go to class, pay attention and practice the homework you will do great. Lectures are informative and he is great at answering any questions. Tests can be a little tricky but if you put in the effort you will do great. Your grade is based on 3 tests so make sure to understand the material. Awesome professor!

Awesome professor. He is crystal clear and will take the time to answer questions. Talks somewhat soft however, so pay attention. Very funny guy. Both 207 and 208 had just 3 exams and nothing else. He says you cannot cram, however it is possible. I've never done one of his hw assignments (which aren't mandatory) and i've received A's on everything.

Matt is by far the best in his department, knows the material inside out and upside down. Funny, dry kinda guy. He will convert stats into knowledge you will actually use. 3 difficult exams, no other points. Attend class, participate, ask questions, do the suggested homework following his examples in class SUCCESS.

What a terrible professor.  He is great about e-mailing you back if you have questions, but his exams are intense, and extremely hard, and don't follow the questions in the book.  I was warned not to take him, and I still did, and regret it. Take a different stats professor if given the opportunity!!

Definitely NOT an easy class. The grade's based on 3 exams. He stopped doing quiz and assignment points. Tests are tough and don't reflect the textbook. But he's helpful if you send him emails with your question. The way to succeed on his tests is to understand what his questions will be like since it's different from the textbooks wording.

Doc Wilk is the best prof on campus, as far as teaching in a way that will set you up for success on the exams and therefore the class. In 207 you will have pop quizzes, which all together are about 25% of your grade, so do the homework. In 208 he does away with this and only gives 3 exams worth 100 pts each. Do homework and attend class to get A

This class wasn't too bad.  You do 90% of the hw using PhStat/Excel, which I thought was great and more relevant to what we'll do in our careers.  Do the hw even though he doesn't grade it.  Go to class.  His tests (especially the 2nd one) can be kind of tricky, especially if you haven't done the homework at all.  He has an awesome sense of humor!
He is a wonderful professor. Highly recommend!
He is the best teacher at Boise State and I feel bad for anyone that doesn't have him

I'm a junior now and this is by far the best professor I've ever had. He explains exactly what you need to learn. If you do the homework, and especially make sure that you understand the story problems, you will do just fine. Now there is the catch, if you can call it that. Homework and attendance become almost essential if you want to succeed.

Go to class, pay attention, and ask questions and you will do great. Very helpful people just choose not to ask when they get lost because they're afraid to become a target to his dry sense of humor, which he will do if he learns your name. Funny guy though I really enjoyed his personality and could tell he really cared we learned something.
Dry sense of humor but funny, if you are sensitive, this may not be the class for you.  Good instructor but make sure you go to class and do the homework.  If you don't - do not expect to pass.

Matt's a good teacher. It's a hard subject to teach, and I think he hit the mark. The second test he gives is so hard. He doesn't curve tests either. It's pretty hard to get an A in this class. I would recommend doing it in the summer.

he has a great dry sense of humor. don't take from him if you are a sensitive nancy, i thought he was awesome. the material is hard but he is willing to help every step of the way if you aren't a jackass
If you go to every class and do the optional homework problems then you will pass. Three exams make up the points for the entire class. The exams can be tricky, so cram.

Great teacher. Likes to call on people in class, but it's just to keep people engaged in the lecture. Very funny and made lectures interesting. I asked lots of questions during lectures and he was always willing to clarify things. First test easy, rest are hard so make sure you study. he gives you all the formulas.recommend summer session(no quizs)

Great teacher, very willing to help those who need it.  always responds to emails quickly, patient with those who have a hard time with it. funny & engaging.  heavy use of textbook, but explains somewhat differently than text. textbook has a lot of errors--as he will point out. not an easy A...not a class for slackers. show up, do the suggested HW

great teacher, makes confusing material easy to understand. attend class and actually do the homework you will be fine.  he always responds to emails and is more than willing to help you.  all you have to do is ask him.  will be taking him for 208 in the fall

Good prof. Likes to make fun of the students that can handle it. Class is a must if you want to pass. He skips a lot of things in the book. Don't read it, it will confuse you! Awesome professor. Very clear cut, to the point, and humorous. His teaching style may be hard for people that don't get math very easily. Tests are sort of hard... he makes all the problems into story problems.

He is likable but not that great a teacher.  He spends a lot of time pounding concepts into your head but then the test looks completely different.  On test review days, don't bother coming to class because you will be more confused than before.

His class is hard if you dont pay attention of make an effort to actually engage yourself in the material. If you study beyond the "mandatory" hw questions and e-mail questions..he's extremely helpful and I did great on the exams. Dont be lazy

This instructor is ill-prepared, uninterested, and a complete waste of time for a student.
Matt's tests can be tricky but if you do your homework and come to class you will get a B or A. All the work is from Excel & PHSTAT. No memorizing formulas.

Online History 101 class. He picks out every mistake that you make such as forgetting one letter in a name and posts it under your comment. He has nothing nice to say only negative things. He does not encourage students to do well and is very particular. Take a different history class.

Amazing! A professor every history major should take.  He is passionate about the art OF history.

He lets you know that he is he webmaster for BSU and that it is his full time job but it doesn't interfere with the class.  If he didn't tell you wouldn't know.  Will take a class from him again!!

Very helpful!  Engaged in the online discussions. He doesn't just give you a syllabus and then forget about you. He makes you think about what you think you know and makes you back up what you say. Awesome teacher!!!!

Great teacher.  friendly and helpful

Great Professor. Friendly, interesting labs, fair grading. She explains importance of techiques and shows how to get equations right.  She is also understanding of personal situations. Take her-you will love the class.

worst professor i have ever had. she refused to answer any questions telling me each time to "look in my book".  she also didn't teach, but rather read power points to the class. i learned nothing from her, and when i retook the class i got an A

great teacher...had to retake chem and learned alot in her class.  She is willing to stay after class to talk about concepts I didn't understand.  Very helpful.  Recommend.  Tests are challenging but she prepares you with problem sets.

He sounds like a native speaker. He's very perceptive to the needs of the class and will change his lesson plan if needed.  I recommend him!

Tom is a great teacher. He is funny, wants you to do well, makes everything very clear, tells you what to expect, very fair grader, and up to date. He is one of the best teachers I have ever had. I highly recommend him.
Tom is an incredibly nice guy and a great teacher. He is very organized and wants everyone to do well. He makes things very clear and enjoyable. I would recommend him to any French student.
He's soo fun and he is very easy going and helpful. if you need a professor for French I highly reccomend him

comment: She is an amazing teacher! Don't bother buying the book for micro, she only tests over the material she lectures. Tests are easy if you go to class and take notes. I got over 100% on all the tests and didn't have to take the final.

She is AMAZING. Take her class and you will not regret it. Tests off of concept understanding and uses homework problems and review questions on the exams. Great teacher!
Kristen is probably the best teacher I've ever had at Boise State. This woman is hilariously awesome and the class is so easy. Take microbiology from her!
She truly loves the subject she teaches and it shows, she also wants her students to do well. Amazing teacher

She is very helpful and wants everyone to succeed. Know the information and how to apply it. Tests have written essays, and vocab. Difficult information to learn but she tries her best to make the class fun and she repeats a lot which is helpful.

Hands down the best teacher I've had at BSU. She cares deeply about the success of her students and goes great lengths to help you get the grade you want. If you show up in class and study her reviews, it's hard to not ace the class. I learned a lot and would highly recommend her.
Kristin is straight-forward about what she expects in the class, and she sets the students up to do very well by making her expectations clear. She is a good teacher and has a wonderful personality.

Toxicology was a great class, and Kristen was a very knowledgeable professor. She tried to incorporate a lot of different historical perspectives into the lectures, which was nice. Super helpful and wants all students to do well. Makes what could be very difficult material more manageable. Her fun personality makes lecture more bearable.

Very good instructor. There is a LOT of material covered in this class, and you are expected to know it. Tests are challenging, requiring you to apply what you know and not simply regurgitate knowledge. Weekly online quizzes and assignments; the lab is pretty simple.

She is a very good instructor and explains complicated material very simply. Her notes are what will be on the tests. It is alot of material to cover but as long as you attend and do the review you should pass. Her tests are not easy.

She is the best teacher I have ever had. I would recommend her for any class. You learn alot of material, but she makes it fairly easy. Makes her own power points and tests over them. I want to take all of my classes from her.
A super easy class, but made interesting by Dr. Mitchell's enthusiasm and organization. If you have to take bio 205, take it from her!

Great teacher. Helpful. Tests from powerpoints. Does a review of previous lecture info at beginning of each class. Creates practice tests and review sheets on blackboard. She is a great teacher. Very interesting and has a good personality. She is very helpful and easy to talk to. Puts all the notes on line and writes tests using her notes. She wants everyone to do good. I would definitely recommend her to anyone and will be taking another class from her.

Dr. MItchell was fantastic!  She loves what she teaches and does her best to get you to love it too. comment: Norm might be my favorite person. I would take any of his classes, even a subject I hated would be alright with him. He encourages discussion and is dedicated to making sure his students learn.
