He brought new to meaning to lit, art, music, and above all, education. BSU doesn't know what to do with that talent.

He scribbles on the whiteboard to try to emphasize his point but there really was none. I learned almost nothing about canada from the class, it is not a history course. All we do is just compare the ignorant American to the multi-cultural Canadian. The last day we all eat Canadian food though which was could've fun.

Moorman is a great teacher with a great attitude. He was one of the best English teachers I have ever had. He is really easy going and has a great sense of humor. He has a pretty strict attendance policy, but otherwise is awesome. I would highly recommend him! He is also the English teacher for CWI.

I took Eng 102 and Creative Writing from Mr. Moorman. It was the best class in both semesters and he is still my favorite professor ever. He calls it like it is but takes a personal interest in students and motivated me to do my very best. He made sure he knew what that was so he could demand it of me  too.

Professor has a specific writing style he prefers. I didn't write in that style and had a hard time trying to figure out what he was looking for due to minimal specific feedback. Class was definitely manageable time wise, and group workshop sessions were valuable.

I actually took him for both 101 and 102. I normally dread taking an English class, but not with his class. Very helpful, kept everyone engaged. Wonderful workshop sessions. I felt like I actually learned something in his class.I would definitely take him again if I had a chance.

Perfect Professor. My favorite class, and I will be taking 102 from him. Easy going, very helpful, funny.  One assignment everyone botched, he gave us two extra weeks to re-do it, and admitted fault. Not afraid to say it like it is, especially when it needs to be said. I would 100% suggest this professor to anyone who takes an ENGL course.
Loved, loved this class. He knows his stuff, and I highly recommend him!
Fun class.  I didn't have an interest in writing prior to this class, but I actually enjoyed myself. I recommend this teacher highly.
The man knows about writing. Of this there is no doubt. His criticism of my work was impeccable and he improved my writing. I get the sense that all the students in my class feel that way.
I really enjoyed his writing class.  The readings we were given were very interesting and when we workshopped our stories he was very helpful.

She taught this class with her husband and there was a total lack of communication throughout. There was very little consistency between the two of them, and they forgot to enter 30% of our homework assignments, they just gave them back with a check mark. They were also unclear on what was do and when, and the expectations of the assignments.
Interesting class. First time it was taught so some confusion on the homework.

There was a serious lack of communication in this class, quite a few guest speakers and not all related to the class which was Intro to Health Professions. We planned 2nd semester ourselves and we never used the book except to take a personality test. She can be too nice at times and doesnt demand respect.
Attendance is not mandatory. The classes are recorded and quizzes online so people can learn without having to get to campus.
Dr Nadelson is committed to assuring her students are successfully prepared to be high quality nurses. Her professional standards and care for students make her a great professor.

Loves to talk about herself and friends.  Gets sidetracked from content very easily!!  Reads directly from slides.  Don't know why attendance was mandatory, could have learned more from the text.  Hard to navigate content thru the you tube videos and personal stories.  Don't disagree or criticize...takes it personally.
No Comments

Interesting class. Liked class discussion. Miller is obviously new to teaching and still figuring things out, but is helpful, caring, and will meet or work with students. Fun watching movies and other Canadian media content. Would recommend.
Hard prof. She expects a lot because it is a 300 level class. fist time teaching and it shows. She's a nice person but not a teacher

Professor Hill, One of the greatest professor in the world. She's funny, outgoing, friendly, and most importantly caring for her students. she is an excellence professor. she sincerely make you feel welcome to ask her anything.

Communications teacher? How about actually being able to talk to a student about his/her issues with an assignment then? This woman is a terrible communicator and very disorganized. She's very condescending and will blatantly make rude remarks to students in front of the entire class. Oh, she won't take your drs note if you're sick, so stay healthy
Jen is an excellent instructor and enjoyable.  She makes the class fun and grades fairly on all assignments.  I would take another class with her anytime!

Jennifer was an exceptional Prof! She allowed enough slack in discussions that we could joke and tell stories of how the material related to our own lives. I am a Non-traditional student and I found that she did not dumb down the lessons to only apply to young students. The take home test was long but it was an open book!!! All the answers are in t

She was aware that in a commuter school like BSU, you should gear your teaching for both traditional and nontraditional students.I also feel like she connected with every student on a very personal level. She heralds critical thinking and mastery of communication, not just for the credit, but for life. Her creativity and passion made this class.

Jenn's teaching style was innovative. I looked forward to this class every week, and it was a Saturday class. She taught a lot more than I expected, we were introduced to and applied critical thinking in every assignment. I feel like I am a proficient and experienced speech writer and speaker after this course. I would recommend this class!

One of the worst professors I've had. She is disorganized, condescending, and very forgetful. The take home tests were ridiculously long and covered material she never taught. Though the class itself was pretty easy, dealing with her was not worth the easy grade.
Fun teacher and good to look at.
Fun class. Must attend class to get a good grade. She doesn't use powerpoint or blackboard though.

Doesn't use PP, tests are taken directly from a test bank provided by the textbook publisher, so if you are doing the readings, the tests are fine. She calls on you in lecture to answer questions, so if you haven't read, you get put on the spot. Overall very supportive and cares about her students and wants you to learn. doesn't use BB.
She really cares about her students.  Can get boring at times, does not use PowerPoint for lectures and her tests are very difficult!

This was a very simple class. Read the text, participate in lectures and take notes. The tests come directly from lecture, she spoon feeds the info. There are 3 papers, but they are opinion papers, very easy.

Fairly new prof that isn't quite sure of herself.  She doesn't like you taking notes during class, but instead being very interactive, but lecture is boring.  Her tests are very hard and so is her grading against essays & the paper!

I rated him a 3 across the board except for helpfulness because I droped his class on the first day.  He wrote the book under a pen name, and corrected the author more than once.  He asked us to refer to him as "Odin" on the syllabus, he went off on tangents, Our line of defense was book, internet, group, class, then him for questions.  Awful.

Show up to class, take notes, pay attention, read the chapters and you will do well in his class.  Has a tendency to ramble but its usually to make a point so you remember it for the tests.  Great professor overall, hated the class at first but came to enjoy it. Learned more in this class than most others.

Took this course online. Great instructor, not easy by any means but I learned a LOT about Econ. Requires mostly essay responses so you have to know the content. Use of BBoard was better than other online courses I have taken. Good class, online worked well. Again, not easy but worth it.

Took it online. Great material! Very useful class. He can be a jerk. Will give you assignments that are a waste of time b/c he can. Will also drop group assignments on you during dead week. WATCH OUT! He burys links into links into links. Not the smoothest online professor. I still enjoyed the course.

This guy is no bueno. He rarely goes over what the chapter has and if he does it is about one thing only. It takes him 3 weeks to go over one chapter and rambles on about the same thing throughout the year. If you ask a question, good luck getting a straight answer. The only nice thing is that the final is not accumulative. Read the book.

I like this professor. He knows his stuff and obviously enjoys teaching it. He's always willing to help, and he cares a lot about the students. The tests are pretty tough but if you attend class it's not awful. Seriously it's like listening to your grandpa talk about economics for an hour. It's really not bad, considering I was dreading the class.
the tests are really hard!!

He seems to waste alot of time. He tries to have students interact, but this does not benifit anyone. The tests have nothing to do with the lectures. The take home portions are VERY difficult and have little to do with what is learned in class or reading. BEWARE: the final exam IS the take home, so do well on it and don't expect a final test

Probably one of the easiest professors I've had. I took a 5 week long course from him and not only did I learn everything I needed to merely by attending class, but his tests were pretty much straight from the lecture. The only complaint I have is with how many group assignments he had us do. Those can suck if you have a lazy group.

Only take this class if you enjoy long lectures that often do not pertain to the test. He is very unorganized and is very confusing with his directions. He often posts wrong assignements to blackboard, changes dates of tests just a few days before the exam, and makes students in class feel dumb if they did not answer correctly. Exmas are horrible!
Dr. Hart is a very different instructor. He is very knowledgable, funny and loves to help his students.  His test can be hard and the material can be hard to learn. I would take him again though.

The professor seems hard and unorganized at first.  As the class progressed, he is a very fair, easy and knowledgeable professor.  If you go to class, study some, do the assignments, you will get at least a B.  He gave everyone the option of either taking the final or opting out and keeping the grade you have  .  I would take him again.
Dr. Hart is a really hard teacher. I had a hard time with his class. But he cares.

Dr. Hart is a hard teacher and if you do not go to class or do any of the work then yeah you are going to have problems with his class. his test are hard there is no denying that and he is willing to help anyone who needs help... if you communicate with him in a timely manner than he will recipricate. I loved his class and he really helped me under
Bless his soul, the man has no grasp of email or computers.  So when it comes to submiting assignments online or take home exams, be prepared to be frustrated.

I took Dr. Harts econ class last semester and he was so helpful(since it was my second time taking the class, from a different teacher)I am taking his macro class right now and he is very helpful his way of teaching makes it so you understand the material the test are hard but if you go to class and read the chapters they should be a little easier

I liked Dr. Hart enough to take another Economics class from him. He is very approachable and has a different style of teaching that helps you really learn the material. He is very knowledgable and if you don't mind his tangents which are examples to help people understand then go to class, take notes and read the book you will do well.
A course everyone should take. He makes it apply to everyday life. GREAT class!
great professor. has incredible knowledge of the subject and you can tell that he likes teaching the subject. just show up and pay attention in class and you will do fine.
Great professor! He knows the material front and back. If you read the book and write down material talked about in class you'll do well. I truly understand Microeconomics after his class.
Great teacher. Down to earth and cuts through all the crap. Sound understanding of economics and wants students to do well.
This class is so easy if you attend. He is the nicest teacher I have ever had, and he made sure everyone understood how important econ is. GREAT CLASS!

Best teacher I have ever had! If you go to class and do your reading the class is a breeze. The only class i have never missed. I have taken 2 classes from him and wished he taught more! You just need to read and pay attention and you will understand. He made me want to be an economist! Highly Reccomend

The class isn't a breeze, but the professor will make sure EVERYONE understands the topic before moving on.  Teaches in a class discussion environment. Wont mark down for attendance, but if you are diligent about going, you WILL pass the class.  Very funny, and easy going with deep understanding of the Topic.
Very sweet man and understanding.  I enjoyed coming to his class because it's like listening to your grandpa about how the world works.
Not my bag of tea.
No Comments

Cost is a difficult class, regardless of who's teaching it.  Celia is very nice and I enjoyed her class.  The homework can be difficult and time consuming (it's basically 206 all over again), but luckily she tended to give us less complicated problems on the (lengthy!) exams.  Go to class, TRY do the hw.  She goes over parts of the hw in class.
Very nice lady who seems to be very busy. Took forever to get feedback/grades on assignments.

I agree with the last 3 reviews.  Her assignment descriptions are less than clear, to put it very nicely.  And then she has the audacity to grade them very strictly.  Her comments are hilarious, what she critiques people on is borderline ridiculous, based on her assignment descriptions.  She expects you to read her mind.  She's a poor communicator.

Really nice lady who is willing to help, but the topics are just so boring.  Online class wasn't too hard - but she would reuse instruction videos and assignments from previous semesters without changing them at all, so it would get confusing as to what she really wanted.  But the class actually got easier and easier the more you get used to it.

Not great at explaining assignments. Grading was a little vague. Tests were brutal and way too subjective. She tried to take stuff out of the book but the multiple choices would not be that simple. I am not quite sure she has that much applied experience with some of this material. Nice lady and she does try hard.

Very nice person. Topic is boring, but not her fault. Her assignments were very vague. Her lectures didn't help. Takes forever to grade assignments and give feed back, but she was overloaded this semester. Tests grades were horrible for most students. Grading on papers was inconsistent. I am just glad it's over.

Celia is a sound professor.  She is helpful.  This class is lengthy in material, but it is not overly difficult.  At time lectures were a little unhelpful or lacking pertinent instruction for homework, but she checks her email regularly and is very helpful.  She is also very professional and respects her students.  I would recommend her!
I think Celia is a great professor; the class is a little too boring and pointless for me.  I think it would be that way no matter who taught it.
No Comments

Worst professor at BSU 10 exams in the class all are essays you take home and write out. Repeats the same material over and over in lectures Very strict teacher when it comes to grading your exams On his syllabus it says that attendance isnt mandatory but will take attendance when less than 10 people show up to class to force more students to come
Stay away from this guy. I had to write 14 essays plus a final paper. He is slow on grading assignments and repeats himself all the time. STAY AWAY!!

HORRIBLE.  Grades all of the essays that you write (8 of them) like english papers, and he basically rips them to shreds with comments about things you did wrong...yet he can barely speak english himself.  AVOID!! I didn't learn anything from this class. He is not even nice.
Avoid him like the plague!!!!! His accent is hard to understand and I had to write 8 essays. He had a lot of required reading. Got a B+

This guy is unnerving. He stutters and says "eh, eh, eh," in a peruvian accent and loves herodotus. The pdfs were a nighmare to read. I had to write 8 essays in his class and he spoke the whole class period. Some head scratching timelines haha. You can get a good grade just do the work and read for quizzes.

It is hard to understand him because of his accent. Many documents he sent us were riddled with tons of grammatical and spelling errors. he would  at times lecture all class period about information irrelevant to the class material. he would normally e-mail you with anywhere from 20 to 5 pdfs you would have to print off and read each week. horrible
Worst prof ever... a lot of his materials were useless and made you read a lot! Though his tests are take home exams (essays)

I would avoid this guy if you can. His class isn't that difficult but his lectures are really boring, and I had an interest in the subject. The workload is pretty heavy, which wasn't so bad, but he would email the homework assignments to students, sometimes not getting them to us until as late as 8:30 pm
Hard class, doesn't make sense at all, many PDF's (and he expects you to read them) and is aways taking about who knows what...

Awful is the only way to describe him. Boring lecture, unclear, talks about the same thing the entire time but expects you to be an expert. Can't speak proper English but expects you to write perfectly. Many books to read! Lastly, the semester is not over & he has e-mailed me over 25x's with PDF files to print and read in one day! DO NOT TAKE HIM!
Very uninteresting class.

A native of Peru, Nicanor Dominguez is INCREDIBLY hard to understand and very boring. Quizzes and tests are all take home, which is nice. He uses improper grammar and punct. on the quiz but expects you to write perfectly (like he would know). His grading seems random. Sometimes takes roll and gives points. 3 books required.

I was very excited to take this class at first. Unfortunately, the class ended up being very difficult to sit through. Many quizzes - all take-home. Long, uninteresting lectures and videos, never lets class out on time. He also takes forever to hand back assignments. Attendence is taken at random, though nothing is really learned in lectures.

DO NOT TAKE HIM. Lectures are super boring and seem to have NOTHING to do with the assignments. All exams/quizzes are take home but they aren't super easy and are all essays. he thinks he is an english teacher too because he grades very strict on papers! take history from an easier teacher. i feel like i havent learned much at all  from him

Lectures through the whole class period without giving anyone time to even ask questions or discuss anything. Has strong Spanish still in his speech and will mark you down in your papers if you use contractions, but he will not tell you that at start of class. Took forever to get papers back to us. Grading unclear

The class I took was not what I expected it to be. It was boring, repetitive and I kept falling asleep everyday that I came in and he kept referring to the book as if he worshipped it. It's an interesting class but be prepared to take a nap in it if you're one of those type of people who are tired of repetitive professors

I took this as a summer class and my first impression was that he was interesting and seemed nice. Although he IS both, his class killed me.  Things became redundant when it came to assignments-- no joke, there were papers due everyday (some short, some longer) over BOTH the lecture and reading. We didn't get any of the papers back till almost the

He often would slip in to Spanish while lecturing and be upset when we didn't' know what he meant. Was never on topic. Never discussed the readings in class, and his tests did not cover anything we had covered in class.He took role, but never made his lectures worth attending.

Nice, funny, smart, can't recommend. Repeats same point for 15-20 mins, off topic for long time. Assigned 2 books & 5-6 page essays on each, but never them made relevant in lecture. 6 weeks to return essays, grading vague. 2 textbooks! 'Pop-quizzes' are 5-6 question take home written. Essay exams. Makes mistakes when correcting your spelling.
amazing  teacher
Awesome teacher! Makes class fun, and it's pretty easy if you do all the work and show up to class.

Super nice, really cares, fun and enthusiastic. She will help you as much as you need. Grade is based on showing up & doing the work on time so if you do that, it's an easy "A". I'd take another class from her for sure.

I took play analysis with Gordan. Most of the class is him lecturing, but he is very open to the class guiding his lectures-- if you ask him for clarification, he will give good clarification. I find his lectures engaging.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Graded by few things--Lecture heavy

comment: He is an amazing professor. He is engaging, he knows a lot about theatre, and he makes the class fun. He inspires me with how much he knows about theatre; I want to expand my knowledge on theatre just as much as he has cause I am a Theatre Arts major(:
He is awesome!! Always funny, but he definitely know what he's talking about; it was great to have a professor that actually WANTS to be there!

This professor teaches subjective issues in a manner which sets students up for failure if they do not agree with his viewpoint. He is unclear about his expectations and uneven in his treatment of students. Avoid this class like the plague.
Best professor in the universe. So funny,really smart, makes the class incredibly fun. I learned more from him than all my other classes combined. Everyone was so sad to have this class with him end.

Took A&P with Adams at his current school, Briar Cliff. He is the worst professor I've ever had. Great guy, AWFUL teacher. His tests are nearly impossible, he offers absolutely no extra credit, and his workload is absurd. He made A&P so miserable for me that I changed majors. Don't plan on getting an A in this class, it's nearly impossible.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Jason is a really nice guy. It shows that he really wants each student to do well on the lab exams. As long as you are willing to put a little bit of work, he we do all he can to make sure you understand the material. As for the tests, as long as you study you should have no problem.

What a waste of time!  This guy is really nice but his teaching style is confusing.  He does not explain himself well and the material is simply regurgitated rather than explained or reasoned out to understand.  I was never clear if this guy understood what he taught.  I would recommend taking this class from the instructor of your lecture class.

This instructor taught 227 lab.  He is nice; however, his instruction is extremely confusing.  Material he talks about is not clear and it makes taking a test tough - I found I had to ignore lectures he gave to do well on tests.  At end of course he did not give eval - I think he knew they wouldn't be favorable.

Honestly not a big fan of this guy. I can see how some people enjoy his lectures and discussions, but that's about it. Poor response time with emails. Cancelled class a lot, which really took away from the learning experience for an intense theory course. Avoid taking him if you can help it.

He is an awesome teacher.  I took his so 230 class this semester and the books we read and discussions we had in my class I will never forget. He is an awesome and well educated teacher. Take a class from this professor if you need the credit. Great and interesting class. I have enjoyed it.

I honestly do not like this professor at all! He is confusing and probably one of the worst upper division classes I have ever taken. He seems to be under the illusion that upper division means graduate level? Do NOT take him if you can help it! Wish I had dropped the class when I had the chance. Two tests, one paper, and an awfully slow grader.
I read and went to class and the exams were 85 questions.. its hard for a 102 class! He is mono toned and boring. The videos are interesting though.

Very approachable and clear about what's expected. Tests are open book but you still need to study for them beforehand. Two or three in-class videos that you write a paper on. Offers lots of extra but the extra credit takes a lot of effort. Very organized, good quality class in my opinion.

I only used the textbook to study for tests, we never opened them in class. His lectures can be extremely boring! There isn't that much work in the class, so each assignment and test are worth a lot. He does offer extra credit, but it's a lot for a little bit of points.
Social problems was a fascinating subject. He made class interesting and I actually looked forward it. I would recommend this teacher

i liked him in the beginning and found things interesting in his class. our only assignments were a midterm and a research project, he doesnt help with anything outside of class. e mailed him many times with questions about project and never responded. never received my research paper back nor did i get a response on it. i dont recommend him

Reads directly off notes for whole lecture, very boring. Topics are very interesting but spends too much time talking about issues he is passionate about (Latinos) and less about thinks he doesnt think are important but others may. Not helpful outside of class, offers to put videos in Library so if you miss the video you can watch it-never does it!

Awesome professor, he very interesting, I learned a lot from him.  Would love to take soc302 from him, unfortunately he is not teaching it this semester.  Tests were hard, but as long as you study for them and pay attention in class you can do well.  Would highly recommend this teacher to anyone who is interested in pursuing a degree in Sociology.

He is really monotone and its hard to not fall asleep. Slides were somewhat confusing and he just reads out of the book. For Exams must know vocab and read the chapters to get an A. His exams ask alot of true or false and definitions. He offers a ton of extra credit. Overall was an easy class.
Has a lot of information. Exam format was confusing, but enjoyed his class.
Had an atmosphere open for discussion. was open to hearning ideas, opinions, and comments. Gave graet feedback. Had high expectations.

Very interesting class. Not too sure why folks say even if you study you won't get a good grade...if you attended class, read the assignments, and paid attention, you'd do well. Enjoyed his lectures and descriptions of cases he had worked on. Would take him again.
Very Good Lectures.  Tests are hard even if you study, quizzes are not too bad.  Assignments are time consuming but interesting.  Goes off tangent quite a bit.

Not an easy A or B. Lectures were informative and entertaining. Both his quizzes and exams are multiple choice, but they're still very difficult. Had to write a paper on attending an oral argument and a non-fiction book with some kind of trial component. Both papers were easy A's as long as you worked hard on them.

Dr. Martin is a massive asset to BSU.  Her depth of knowledge is without equal.  I told her openly in class I hated the class's subject and she laughed instead of getting angry. Write well and you will do well. Do the readings and contribute to class discussion. Dr. Marin is inspiring and incredibly helpful. I wish she taught more classes @ BSU!

dr. martin is fantastic. hard work required but very rewarding. she is brilliant but never stuffy, and always enjoyable and enthusiastic about the topic. she lets students pursue their own interests within the framework of the class and always seems interested in what you say even if you are an idiot

Very knowledgeable, usually interesting. Also, kind & sweet besides. Class format=pure discussion, so 1) do the reading 2) participate x100, it is key to your grade, and also will influence hugely what you'll learn/retain. Be prepared also to write a fair bit in this class.

Lots of busy work, no test exams, but you still need to attend class in order to not miss the free writes.  The free writes are worth points and make up the bulk of points you receive for the course.  Instructor is very nice and helpful.
Great teaacher/nurse. She wants everyone to do well and genuinely seems to care.
Great teacher, great enthusiasm
If you are taking her online course Human Growth and Development all you have to do is read the book, and you can't help but get an A in the course.

This class was a telecourse so the lectures were watch on BSU channel 95 (Cable).  The lectures were not necessary to watch as 99% of test was from text book.  Tests were vague and instructors never went over them in lecture after test.  You had to make appt to see them in their ofc.  Weekly assignments were busy work.  Easy A folks!
Its a pass or fail lab but shes super nice. She helped us understand what was real world info and what was test only info. She sent a lot of time making sure we knew what we needed to know.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Clear grading criteria

comment: This class now has tests and they are HARD!

Great person, very informative on the subject she teaches.  This class does not have test exams; however, you still need to attend as you get your points through "free writes" at the end of random classes - you must go or you may miss a free write and the points you receive for doing it.  A lot of work was busy work, but you will learn something.
No Comments

It is an easy "A".  The assignments were nothing more than busy work and tests were simple - everything came from the book.  Rarely did anything from lecture appear on the tests.  Instructors never went over tests and said to come to their ofc to review tests.  Pointless when it was a telecourse - the point of it is to not go to campus! Ugh!

He is a nice guy who knows a lot but DO NOT take his class.  He doesn't grade anything but assigns so much reading.  I did all the reading for his classes but struggled with his weird quiz questions.  I spent more time on his class than all my other classes combined, just trying to keep up.  There's no course schedule or rubrics.  So stressful.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: 90% of my effort last semester went in to  this class. Steve was understanding with giving extensions,  but grading guidelines were incredibly vague. Most of my assignments weren't graded until weeks after the fact (the first wasn't done until after midterms) Hundreds of pages of reading and multiple essays each week. Avoid if possible.

He seems like a really nice guy, but he is an incredibly difficult professor. Im in his online course and when he says to expect 15 hours a week, expect 15 or more. You will be reading SO MUCH that you won't have time for other classes. I feel bad since he seems so nice when I ask him questions through email, but he expects WAY too much.

If you have the opportunity to take Steve Barrett, run far away and don't do it. The class was ridiculous, the grading was inconsistent, there was virtually no syllabus and whenever you attempted to ask a question or for him to clarify his expectations, he would tell you to turn in whatever you come up with... and then would fail you.

This guy gave the most difficult midterm I've ever taken. I'm a senior, 1440 old SAT, and this kicked my ass.  Very smart, good lectures, but he lets students teach most of the class each week as "presentations," assigns 100+ pages per week of reading, and expects incredible recall on quizzes and homework. And he does not grade easy on the quizzes.

Prof. Hindrichs is very knowledgeable and passionate about literature. That being said, she can be critical on the analysis assignments but her feedback is solid. There is a lot of reading and discussion board participation required but definitely worth the time as we got to engage with a lot of great works. Units were 2 weeks long which was nice.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Cheryl was a very hard grader. She refuses to give you a 100% on anything. No matter how hard you work she will still find something to knock points off for. Its a 100 level class and she grades 10x harder than any of my senior level teachers. She also will set a rubric and when you follow exactly that she will still knock you down for something.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Tough grader

comment: Cheryl knows how to make a boring class super fun. 268 is based heavily on reading from old British literature and can be very dull and dry at times, however as long as you read what is required of you and take a little time to think over what you just read, then you should be fine.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Hilarious

comment: Cheryl rocked my world this semester. Seriously, one of the best classes I have ever taken and probably my favorite professor at BSU. There is a lot of reading in this class, but 100% worth it. You will get so much out of it. Take as many classes with Cheryl as you can! She is freaking hilarious and absolutely brilliant!!
Cheryl is seriously THE BEST. This is a hard class and you have to work, but it is so so so worth it. You will learn a ton and laugh A LOT. She is hilarious and such a nice lady. Take this class!!

Engaging, interesting, and helpful. This class focuses on exposure to and thought about literature and very little on composition (it's a 200, be real). So far, this was the best class and best professor I've had at BSU. Cheryl has my highest rating. Be warned, you will be expected to share your interpretations and be versed in composition.
Cheryl is the freshest.

Prof. Hindrichs is an extraordinary teacher who demands a lot out of her students. In this difficult class you will learn an immense appreciation for literature, as well learn how to overcome very difficult readings and writing assignments. Great Professor.

Cheryl is my favorite professor that I've ever had. She's smart, witty, and she is genuinely passionate about her subject. They aren't easy classes but they're well worth it. You won't just learn rote facts, you'll learn new ways of thinking about yourself and about life.

I honestly LEARNED. She knows her stuff. Be prepared to work your butt off! As long as you give it your best and you demonstrate an understanding you will get a good grade. The other key is to participate in the class discussion- helps your grade a lot.

She is very smart but also very unrealistic. I had a 99% in the class and for the final she gives one hour and 15 mins for two essay questions and 10 short answers and no one finished. So you work hard all semester for her to just destroy your grade at the end. Take this class if you like getting screwed over.

Amazing professor. I also took her Engl 268 class. She is very intelligent and very knowledgeable in the subject matter. She is also very passionate about it. Criticism and Theory was really tough but was very rewarding. I learned a lot from her in both courses. I HIGHLY recommend her for any lit class.

As already stated on here, she is almost intimidatingly smart and very funny. If you attend class and put a little effort into your work, you will receive high marks. For being a teacher that really requires in-depth analysis, she goes easy on you when grading as long as you try.

Cheryl is very knowledge about her subject but her level of thinking is much higher than many students. A lot of things covered went over my head. She likes to think way in depth. Exams very hard. Must attend class.

Cheryl is wicked smart & funny (she has an awesome dry wit). She's open to student ideas & interpretations, but will definitely tell you when you're way off (Lit theory is complex & she knows her stuff). Material is difficult & there is an insane amount of reading, but when you're done you come out of it with a solid foundation in literary theory.

Cheryl is brilliant, just insanely smart, knows her subject and  she is really, really funny. That said, there is a sense that while she'll listen to students' ideas about literature, in the end, she's right. It's just something in the way she looks at you. Still, take her class, you'll learn a lot and laugh too.

In my opinion, she is not an open-minded person. If you are a sheep, this is the class for you. Other opinions will not be tolerated. Degradation is part of her curriculum. I would not recommend her for students who take pride in their morality.

A demanding instructor who really does want you to enjoy the subject as much as she does. I went into the class stating that I hated (used lightly here) and came out loving the subject. Her class requires an open mind, and a lot of work, but the rewards are, in my humble estimation, immeasurable.

Great teacher: very knowledgeable, enthusiastic, helpful. I think the grading on written work is a bit too lenient, but her feedback/constructive criticism is super. The material (lit theory) is difficult and can be v. frustrating, so be prepared to read dense writing and work hard --but it is so, so worth it/valuable.

This class is not for the faint of heart! That said, Prof. Hindrichs is an amazing, engaging, humorous, friendly, incredibly knowledgeable and sincere teacher. I worked very hard in this class- lots and lots of tough reading, a few in-depth papers, and a TON of class participation. But all worth it- everything was relevant to my studies even now.

Mary Ann is a very sweet lady, but she is not knowledgeable at all in OB.  She has never worked in the field and has very outdated information.  She doesn't present information well and tests very difficult and off of information that she personally didn't cover in class.  Just teach yourself and don't attend lecture.

Mary Anne is a great professor with a lot of compassion for her students and for nursing.  She is very well organized and is always available to visit with her students; whether it is for help with class or advice about school.

She is a very funny instructor and easy going.  Majority of problems are story-type problems.  I would have liked to see opportunities for some extra credit because if you mess up one or two quizzes, your shot for an A is out the door.  This class could have been offered online as lectures were not useful.
What a sweet lady.  She was very friendly and very funny.  The material was straight forward.  I would have liked to see an extra credit or two to do assignments, but otherwise great class.
MaryAnn is a very nice professor and very helpful.  I really enjoyed her class and felt like I learned a ton!
Content was easy and straightforward. Not the most helpful or friendly person.

Don't listen to the person below. Mary Ann is a nice lady and she's very fair. From the start she said she didn't like the book & doesn't have a choice because its summer class. Growth & devel is not black & white so things can be interpreted. We have nice discussions in class & Mary Ann doesn't have a problem if others disagree with her.

The class is mandatory if you want to pass. She doesn't take attendance but does do pop quizzes. She goes very fast through explanations. She writes every problem and definition out on the board and her handwriting is horrible and hard to read.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--TEST HEAVY

comment: this teacher can only be described as terrible. her husband teaches the same course and it 5x easier. she is very bland and hard to pay attention to.

You'll take lots of notes. She expects you to understand basic concepts and that's why she moves so quickly in her lectures. The lectures are boring. There are several pop quizzes. Exams are worth a lot of your grade. She's nice and willing to help during office hours. If you wanna pass this class, make friends/study groups.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Speaks in monotone and seems like she hates her job. Does the bare minimum to be considered a "teacher." Her lectures are super boring and her writing on the board is very sloppy which makes it hard to follow. Doesn't prepare well for the tests at all which is worth A LOT of your grade. Don't recommend taking her for this subject.
ratingTags: BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: TERRIBLE TEACHER. She does not want you to succeed. She comes in and teaches a problem once, and then prepares to take a similar problem and make it 3x harder and put it on the test 3 weeks later. She will miss class AND give you tests earlier than other classes AND they are harder. No multiple choice, makes you do excel work by hand unnecessarily.
ratingTags: BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Very monotone and unprepared for class. She is late to class every day and lets class out early too. I wish I did not take the class with her because she does not teach at all.
She was incredibly challenging and didn't show much enthusiasm. Many struggled to pass the course. Very test heavy, studied for hours but test were still extremely difficult.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Fry is more like a lecture introducer  that a professor in her ITM class, both 104 and 105 are pretty easy pass courses but don't expect you can get any help from her because she will just tell you to read back the syllabus again. Her classes are required for business majors, so pass the exams and you will be fine COBES

There are only 3 required days of attendance, the first day, the midterm and the final. Professor Fry is hands off the entire semester. You can email her questions, but she will not be of any help. It is best to go to the tutoring lab if you need help. This class was very easy, but a lot of work for a 1 credit course. Class is passfail.
If youre taking her ITM classes I recommend that you dont take it with a full course load already. Midterms and finals are super tough! Its a pass or fail class

Fry is a fantastic teacher for Stats 207 and 208. If students don't do well on a test, she gives an easy (open book) quiz each week until the next test to boost grades. Her lectures are very easy to follow and she writes everything on the board. You also don't need the book if you print the tables off the internet.
The ITM 104105 classes as a whole have a lot of room for improvement. Be sure to do the homework. Prepare for the tests, because they are a huge chunk of your grade.

Susan Fry is a terrible professor and it makes me mad she actually gets paid to "teach" this class. The only time you interact with her is during the orientation, where she's rude and yells at students. Don't bother emailing her any questions regarding grades, assignments,etc. because she will just tell you to go to lab. NOT HELPFUL!

WAY too heavy of a course load for a 1 credit class.  The test reviews were 180 questions and were graded.  She doesn't teach you a single thing, you just figure it out in the simulation trainings, which don't cover a lot of the things required for you to know for the grader projects.
Awesome teacher

She is an amazing professor. She teaches by examples which makes everything very clear. I took this class this summer and there were a total of 2 homework assignments and 3 tests. She allows a front and back note sheet (with anything on it) and for the cumulative final you can bring your note sheets from the previous exams. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

All work is online, the tests are on  campus and they are exactly like the reviews. I dont think she does a good job showing you how to apply it in the job field but the class is easy if you just do the work. Pass/Fail class.

Its a hybrid class. Each one is only one credit but they are the workload of a 3 credit  class. The assignments aren't that hard but they take a while to complete make sure you do all of them. The class isn't on blackboard so its kind of annoying not knowing where you stand. Not a terrible class.
Passed but not satisfied with anything !

I appreciated that she was good about explaining things for students that have questions. Two of her tests resembled her practice exams. Downfall:  We purchased a book with MyStatLab and TopHat and used TopHat once, and MyStatLab 4 times.  A waste

I see her on a weekly basis at my place of work. I enjoyed her class, she had good office hours and was easy to talk to. MyItLab was the difficult part of it with there were things that had to be specific in how you cut and paste and things. I would say take 105/106 together. They are switching to office 2013 in the fall so be aware!

This is a hybrid course, the only time you go in is for two tests. The homework is fairly time consuming. If you prioritize and do the homework ahead of time, you will be fine. Do not wait until Friday night to finish the homework that is due on Saturday, you will have a hard time getting in done in time.

I took ITM 105 and 106 from her.  Class is quite easy as long as you do the work each week.  You have a couple attempts to do the quizzes and the assignments.  Definitely do the reviews before the exams, they have all the questions that might be on them.  I never needed to go to the labs but it was nice to know that help was available if needed.
Content is easy but the program has so many glitches it'll make your head spin and it is unbelievably frustrating.

Susan is fantastic. she doesn't really lecture but teaches by examples. classes get out early and tests are easy. full page of notes front and back for exams. no hw. definitely a solid class and prof. I would always recommend her!
Awesome professor, makes the material clear. Allows note card for tests, and open notes for quizzes. Wont keep the class till last second, will let you go once that days material is covered.

She's one of the few teachers who can help the average student navigate their way through such a difficult subject such as Busstat.  She has several quizzes, a few exams, and one project.  Show up to class, take notes, and you'll be fine.  Take this class from her!

Took ITM 104/105/106 at the same time from her. She responded to my emails quickly, and there was alot of available hours to get help in the lab. Coursework was all online, tests on campus. Coursework was pretty heavy for 1 credit classes, so dont expect it to be a breeze, but if you do all the work it is pretty tough to fail.
The first 4-6 weeks is hard, then it will get easier as the semester goes on. Good explainer. Prep for tests, take good notes, and go to class and you should get an A.
Susan is an amazing professor! IF you have the chance to take her class, I highly recommend it! Easy class as long as you attend everyday. Will not regret! Makes stats a piece of cake!! :)

The easiest class I have even taken. She is so easy. You dont need book for this class. All you need is your notes. Easy exams and she lets you use the notes for the exam. She grades the exam really easy too. If you miss the quizzes, just talk to her and she let you take those quizzes again. Attendance is not mandatory but you shud take the notes

I took all 3 ITM courses. They're hybrid courses, so expect a lot of self-learning. I never did see her while taking the classes, but she did have office hours listed on the syllabus. I just never needed to go in. Lab hours are very helpful with her assistants. Orientation and 2 exams are mandatory attendance. Do your work and you have an easy A.

As a prior student for the ITM courses, I can honestly say that the students who mostly write negative reviews are probably the students who never did any of the work.  There are lab hours for homework questions but still many do not use them.  Just pay attention the first day and set aside time for the assignments and you will pass!

BEST stats teacher there! TAKE HER! Easy tests, always there to help. Just GO to class! She gives out pop quizzes, but let's you use notes. Tests/Quizzes aren't hard at all if you actually go to class and take notes/pay attention. Great teacher, and you know she's good because her class is already on wait list for next semester!
She is not a very thoght teacher. problems on the exams are from the notes she gives in the class.
worst professor
Great professor.  I don't like stats, but I managed to get through her class with a B which was more then I could have asked for.  She is the best Stats professor!!!
Very nice teacher. Her class is difficult, but it isn't her fault. She teaches what you need to know. Cheat sheets can be used on test. Very reasonable with her tests.
Cheat sheets allowed on tests, very reasonable prof.  teaches only what is necessary and on test.

Susan ROCKS!!  I think she is by far the best teacher I have had at BSU.  I didn't do well the first time I took BUSSTAT, so I had to take it again.  I really think she works hard on helping everyone pass her class. Even extra credit...Take her and you won't be disappointed.

Susan is a great teacher compared to the others at BSU.  She understands that Stats is difficult for some people and really takes the time to help you out and is very clear with her lectures.  She does go a little fast, but you just have to ask questions in class to have some clarity on some topics.  Next semester is BUSSTAT 208 & I'm taking Susan!

Susan Fry is a great teacher she answers e-mails quickly and helps when she can,she has 650 students to grade stuff on so expect to not see her very much it is an online class... it can be hard but if you go to the times in the lab where assistants of hers are there is is very helpful
She is a ghost.  She never came to the required classes.  Everything is online.  WHen i emailed for help she normally didn't say anything that helped.  I taught myself everything.

Susan is one of the best, smartest, and most helpful teachers I have taken at Boise State. She is definitely the teacher to take for Busstat 207 and 208. She allows you to use your notes and gives you regular handouts that are identical to the tests. Busstat is definitely not an easy course, but she does everything and anything to help everyone.

Excellent professor for this course.  She clearly explains the material through in class example problems and handouts. There were unannounced quizzes, but they aren't too difficult, since you can use your book and notes. Students could use a formula sheet on the exams, which helped out alot.

Very good instructor. I sometimes felt that she went too fast through her lectures, but the notes and handouts she gave in class were almost exactly like what was on the exams. She even lets students use a formula sheet on the exams. There is a project due at the end of the semester, but she grades fairly easily if you follow her directions.

We had a few mandatory attendance days, yet she never showed up to any of them. This class is basically a self learning class, all online. I emailed her a few times, and when I got a response it was short, sweet, and you could tell she was annoyed by the language in it. Mandatory class, just don't expect anything from her!

Absolutly waste of my money!... 1200 dollars to take ITM 104/105 *ONLINE nevertheless*... Teacher i guess is a lab instructor but since she didnt show up to any of the required classes I dont know if she's real or fictional. Homework is all from myitlab.com 2 test on campus & from her messages on blackboared we all suck compared ot her. Dont take!!

-random check ins to take attendence -first test is available online -copies powerpoints from other teachers -do not cram. take notes by hand to retain everything he says because he will test you on VERY specific facts -terrible public speaker -tries to make class funny

He's a Geology Prof- this class used to be called Earth Sciences - so he has to cover a lot out of his field. Always ready to admit if he didn't know the answer-I thought the lab was more difficult than the class. Read the text-he doesn't cover everything in class.

Do not take this professor... Worst I have had at Boise State! What you learn is not what is on the tests. Test average was a 65% it was lame. Everyone hated it. The only thing that saved me was the easy lab.

As long as you show up to lab and do really well and also complete various assignments then you will be fine.  My average on his tests was a high F but by getting good grades in all the other areas, I ended up getting a B+ so just keep that in mind because his tests were very difficult for me! No study guide :(

I think Bill is a great teacher! He truly wants students to learn and think. He doesn't give study guides, but he tells you how to study, even posted a large amount of info on BB for tips on studying. True, you don't need to memorize, but you do need to understand the concepts and apply logic when taking tests. 2nd test was hard and he curved it.

I loved this class. It is not an easy A, but if you read the book, take good notes, and use critical thinking on tests you can do fine. I worked hard for my B and feel good about it! I fell in love with the subject. Plus, he is cute in an older, liberal, kind of nerdy way!

Extremely difficult class for a nonmajor class. He expects you to know EVERYTHING in depth on exams, yet if you ask him simple questions in class he often doesn't know the answer. Many assignments seemed to have little to do with Geology. Half of his class seems to be trying to teach you how to be students, instead of teaching Geology.

Not a very interesting, or interested professor.  He does not seem to care wether or not his class succeeds or fails.  he will not give study guides and his tests cover vast amounts of material.  I do not recommend taking him unless you already know a lot about Geology.

class average for exams were always low. tests don't contain terms or definitions. there is no memorizing needed because the exam questions require deep thinking. this class was way too intricate for a 100 level class. i would not recommend taking him.
Worst professor I have had. AVOID if possible. He doesn't give a study guide for tests, it is extremely unclear on what to know for tests. Just an all around bad class!!!
wonderful teacher.
Great guy. He prepares you well for tests if you just attend class every day.

Good teacher to take if you're looking for an easy A. However, if you're actually trying to learn the material, that's a different story.  He only went over 3 problems in a single class period, on average. Sometimes the students have to tell him how to do the problems.  Oh, and he DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO USE A GRAPHING CALCULATOR, he refuses to learn.

Study hard for tests, I am a very good student and only ended up with a B+.  He is funny and lectures in coordination with the book.  He really likes it when you participate and tries to keep class entertaining, with demonstrations.  I would recommend him.

he's a pretty cool professor. he didn't know a whole lot of details, and i think the class would have been better if he was more knowledgeable. overall, i enjoyed it very much, though it was not an easy A.

This is a critical thinking professor. He wants you to read the text book and review the powerpoint slides.  He is always available after class and he's always in his office for questions...Don't take the class if you are looking for an easy A

He is a bit stern and has an East Coast personality which leaves somethings to be desired but all around I loved him. He is intelligent and cracks lame nerdy rock jokes that rock! :)and he dresses nice.

He was very unapproachable. He goes off on tangents and can get VERY distracted! He seems confused with this new job (this is his first year teaching!) He definitely makes you feel stupid if you try to answer any of his questions in class. He is self proclaimed intimidating! I was very frustrated in this class. Definitely wouldn't recommend him!
He did want to help his students.  He was good at the concepts of math but was rusty on arithmatric.  Sometimes the students would have to talk him through the problem when he made a mistake.

Very strong lecturer. It is clear that he is passionate about emag and knows his stuff. Not an easy course, but tests are open book+notes. Very friendly and helpful outside of class. He is also rare in his efforts to prep students for real world work, regularly giving asides about how things are ACTUALLY done at engineering companies!  Outstanding!
Awesome dude.

Tough subject to teach. Also since the course is required most students did not want to be there. If taking Emag theory at Boise state make sure to get this professor. His study sessions make the tests much easier.

This is an extremely hard course to begin with. I felt like Dr. Browning talked fast, but gave a lot of info about the formulas we were using. The tests could get more difficult than they needed to at times. Typical amount of homework, I never felt overwhelmed. Would recommend taking him and only him for this class.
No Comments
Very easy going personality as well as grading

A very fun professor to have for a core class. Gives a nice history of theater with some interesting plays to read. Just show up to class, read the plays assigned and you'll do fine. Provides power-points with all the answers you'll need for the tests. Very nice and a great professor.

Carole is hilarious. She is very laid back and is passionate about what she teaches. She cancelled our third exam as well as let us take a quiz 'as a class' because she knew we all didn't read the play. I would definitely recommend this class for  DLV.

She is such a sweet lady that understands that we have a busy schedule and other upper priority  classes. This class has a open and fun environment to be in. The plays we were required to go to were fun and easy to talk about. Her extra credit opportunities are very frequent and some are easy. There is no textbook in this class to save money.

Carole has such a passion for the theater and it shows when you teach. I was worried about taking this class that it would be boring, but with the way she teach it makes you interested in the subject.
Carole is just a cute little teddy bear. So helpful, and made taking a required theater class entertaining.

My favorite class this semester. Super clear about what she expects, and knows that this isn't a class for your major. She's just trying to give you an appreciation for what she loves, which was why she was so fantastic. Her assignments required thought but were not overly time-consuming, and tests were manageable. Worth getting up for on a Sat AM!
found all the need to read plays on-line. she gives opportunity for extra credit. Her grading is simple and she explains exactly what you need to know, you just have to show up.

She is awesome! She tries to make you excited for theater which coming from someone who doesn't enjoy theater at all, actually made it really interesting. You do need the book or else some way to read a couple plays but honestly just come and don't take crazy notes. This class is NOT hard by any means nor does she expect it to be for anyone. A!

Not a very easy class (for me at least) but this professor is awesome. She is really really passionate about her subject and will lend a hand if asked. Extremely nice and can be funny too. Would I recommend her? Absolutely!

Very passionate about the subject of theatre which is a huge, huge plus. Really cares about her students and wants them to do well, I highly recommend her course if you are in any way interested in theatre.

Carole is  a hoot and very energetic. She brings a lot of her own experiences to class. She really loves theater. Her goal isn?t to create theater majors out of you, but to create an appreciation for the art of theater. She tests from her PowerPoint?s and if you follow the guidelines on the reviews you'll do fine in this class.

For the most part a pretty easy class. Have to attend two plays and write reviews on both. A couple of other writing assignments too plus a creative project. She's very passionate about the subject, just a little scatterbrained. Tests are SUPER easy...they're exactly like the study guide. No textbook.
She was full of energy and theatrical. Made Saturday mornings enjoyable!

She cares a lot about her students, and is always very upbeat and social.  She expects people to share her enthusiasm for theater and if you don't the class can be difficult as well as time consuming!

She is very passionate about theater and tries to pass that on to her students, but doesn't expect everybody to be as into it as she is. She is very bright and cheerful. The class was easy, there were two papers and three tests (multiple choice). Take her if you can bear a Saturday morning class.

The only reason I was able to function at 8am on a Saturday was because of Carole's awesomeness. Required to read about 6 plays, and to attend one. Grading is done by total points which guarantees an A by attending plays for extra credit. Carole is very fun and humorous. I gained clarification in critical writing and an appreciation for theatre.

Carole makes this an extremely fun class. Two mandatory attendances to BSU plays and tons of opportunities for extra credit. Three tests cover  lecture material and reading, but she gives you study guides. If you don't get an "A" in this class the fault is yours. Definitely recommended for Area I.
Great Teacher. Made theater fun. Relativity easy. Helpful. Always in a good mood. Funny. Overall a great class with a woman who has some major talent.

Carole is awesome, she makes theater fun for those of us who aren't theater majors.  She talks about current movies, actors, etc.  She has the rare talent to make old boring plays interesting and connects them to us in today's day and age.  If you have to take an Area I, take THEA 100 from Carole, you won't regret it, you may find you enjoy theater

Fair, motivated, engaging, and kind professor. Yes, the class is hard, but you will be forced to learn. Lots of homework, and you need to put in extra work to get a good grade. Would definitely recommend to first years.

comment: Dr. Henderson was one of my first professors at Boise State. She is absolutely amazing and is very caring towards everyone she encounters. comment: Dr. Henderson assigns a lot of work to do and she is a tough grader. comment: Professor Henderson is by far my favorite professor at BSU. She makes you work for your grade but also makes the class fun and enjoyable. comment: Prof Henderson is an extremely tough grader, but an overall really great professor. comment: Honestly the worst teacher that I have ever had. Most arrogant, stuck up teacher. Grading is extremely hard and very test heavy. comment: Dr. Henderson is very knowledgeable and does a great job teaching this class. She makes lectures very enjoyable and shes hilarious. You do have to work for your grade but that way you will actually learn. 100% recommend for psych majors or anyone who is interested in psychology.

comment: If you do your work and put in effort into understanding the subject, you will do well. She's a really funny professor and you can tell that she really cares about what she teaches. comment: Henderson is an amazing professor. She really cares about her students and has made an amazing impact on me. Her lectures are very engaging. She gives a lot of freedom. comment: She was hilarious and gave engaging lectures. The class was hard but I loved that everything was due on Sunday at the end of the week. comment: Pros: made the most out of class time, kept Lectures interesting, included many engaging activities and group discussion. Cons: Often seemed way over the top and almost rude. Thisprofessor is definitely a hit or miss. I found it hard to put up with her personality. She was just kind of annoying. comment: Professor Henderson is so great! Her lectures are super entertaining and I feel like I have honestly learned a ton this year. The class is very test heavy with little to no homework (besides a weekly quiz) so you really have to make sure you actually read the textbook.

comment: She's really funny, but a lot of homework.

comment: Professor Henderson is unprofessional and close-minded. More than once a student in my class raised their hand to ask a question and was verbally ridiculed by Professor Henderson.
