ratingTags: Get ready to read

comment: Personally, I did not care much for Dr. Henderson. However, her assignments are very clear and it was easy to pass her class. Not the worst choice, but I would not take her again.

She is AMAZING. The best teacher I've had so far. You might think she is going off on some hilarious tangent, but she's actually telling you a personal story that relates to the material! She is very helpful and intelligent, but she's also wild and funny. Attendance is not mandatory for 101, but I recommend that you go anyway! It's always fun.

Do not email her with questions. She answers with terse and rude replies. She uses the psychological method of, "priming" telling students over and over how great a teacher she is. She is not. She is rude and unprofessional and cusses non-stop. I neither respect her as a teacher or a human being. 106

She is an overall nice teacher and I enjoyed her lectures, but you MUST respect the syllabus in this class. She screwed me over with an assignment over a technicality resulting in a much lower grade even though I had done all of the work. Besides that, I would recommend her. She will also try to scare you away on the first day, don't she's EASY.

Make sure you call her Doctor or Professor. Great lecturer, makes things relevant but do not expect to engage in a discussion of psychology beyond a 101 level.  No real world application or controversial ideas. There are tons of assignments, read your book and use it on those assignments, if you do really well on assignments tests barely matter.

Great teacher, super entertaining lectures. She's very funny, but is blunt. It's a lot of information and the exams are very difficult. She's very easy to talk to and answers every question. Not by any means an easy class, so you have to work hard but she'll reward you if you earn it.

There is no B.S. with Dr. Henderson. If you are looking for an easy A, don't take her. You WILL learn a lot from her. I hated the textbook but it's essential to the class. Her lectures are absolutely engaging and entertaining. She is quite humorous but very blunt. You must be a great note taker. Tests are based on NOTES and TEXT. Final was tough.
Good class for incoming freshmen.

Henderson was the best teacher I've ever had. She loves what she teaches and knows how to make it interesting. She does participation so make sure you go to class but it's not a hard lecture to sit through anyway. She says her class is hard but as long as you do participation and study for tests, you're going to be in the clear. Love her!

Kimberly is a great teacher! You will need to put a little bit of work in, but as long as you pay attention you will pass the class. Not to mention it is very easy to pay attention due to the fact she is funny and interactive with the students.

Loved her lectures!! She makes them super entertaining and she is always making jokes. There are a lot of assignments but as long as you do them, it is not too hard to pass the class. Definitely recommend!

I loved this class! She is very funny and also a great lecturer! Questions on the quizzes and tests are based off of what she says in lecture so going is important. Be prepared for the reading checks as they are very specific to the information in the book.

Psych 101 with Henderson is easy to pass if you just do the work. She makes everything very clear in her syllabus. If you need help, she is very willing to help during her office hours. She's very upbeat and funny, and I really enjoyed going to this class. It was never dull. Great professor to learn from in course material and even life.

Dr. Henderson is hands down the most incredible lecturer I've ever had. She is hilarious, relevant, fun, adorable, relatable, and extremely knowledgeable. Everything you need to know about the course is clearly stated in her syllabus and she replies to emails quickly. 1010 highly recommend!

Henderson is a really cool lady! Her lectures are super intriguing, and she makes the course material interesting. This class is definitely not an easy A, you will have to work for it by reading the text and studying. If you're interested in studying Psychology, or just need to get a science credit out of the way, I definitely recommend taking her!

I like this class very much because she keeps you interested by the way she talks. She is very lively and knows her stuff. There are many reading checks and quizzes that you need to keep up on. This class is difficult but is so worth it because you get a lot out of the class.

Professor Henderson is absolutely Hilarious. There were a lot of times I didn't want to go to her lectures but always because of laziness never because of her! She is definitely one of the coolest professors I've had but don't mistake that for her being easy! She's a really tough grader and there is A LOT of homework, participation & quizzes.

Henderson is one of the coolest teachers I've ever had. Her lectures are awesome, and very interesting. The readings are long, but if you go to class and do the assigned homework, you'll be golden. The tests aren't too bad, and there's not very many. I would recommend her to anybody taking a psychology class.

Highly recommend Henderson for any psych class. She makes her lectures interesting & easy to follow. Her grading isn't just over tests, and it is easy to get an A. As long as you attend lecture, this class is extremely easy to follow. I am not even a psych major and I am taking any class that she offers. She truly cares about her students.

Her class was good. The tests aren't the easiest, but very possible to get an A. Just keep on track with the work she assigns. She explains concepts very well, and I am able to grasp everything clearly during lectures. She allows mobile phones and laptops, but we have to be segregated in order to use them. I definitely recommend her.

She is an overall good professor: she's funny, knows the material, etc. Her test are tough, and I honestly don't think they correspond very well with the material that she covers in class. The class is curved though, so just make sure you COMPLETE all assignments and you will be fine. Don't bomb the tests either.
The best professor ever! Loved her can't wait to take another class of hers!

By far one of the best professors I have had, you can tell that she cares about what she is teaching. The class is tough if you don't read and do the quizzes and participation. The only large tests are the midterm and final that is it. Overall an easy class if you just stay on top of the work.
Mrs. Henderson is very cut and dry on how to pass her class: show up, do the homework. Her lectures are educational and entertaining! There is no one better to take Psych from, she is outstanding!

She's an incredible professor! Easy A if you show up and do the handful of assignments she assigns. Mind you it's not a simple a on assignments, you do have to do a through job. Overall AMAZING!!!!!!!!

Lays out the rules in the first class. Tells you exactly how she grades an gives you opportunity to change professors. GREAT lecturer, you can tell she loves to teach and is passionate about the subject.
Awesome

If you're a slacker, avoid this class. Dr. Henderson is a great teacher if you are willing to pay attention. she does all she can to ensure you get an  A in her class except force you to be there. so if you're dedicated to getting an A she is the teacher for you.

She is really funny and makes the material memorable. Her tests have questions based off the lecture so it is important that you go to class. She assigns a lot of homework, that pretty much makes up your grade.
without a doubt the worst professor I have ever had. It seems like she wants the class to fail

She is useless when it comes to getting feedback on how you can do better. When everyone failed her test, her way of curving the test was making us do paragraphs on each question we missed on the test. She makes the online class harder than any other class. Don't email her she is just rude and I really don't care for her as a professor or a person
I love her. She is very clear on what she expects and as long as you pay attention and do your work you will get a passing grade. and she is so entertaining best professor by far i have had.

Excellent professor. Very helpful and understanding when I fell behind due to my wife's emergency surgery. Dr. Henderson worked with me to help me get back on track after missing two weeks of class, although she was the only one to require a doctor's note. Textbook not used in class, but lot's of reading assignments. Highly recommend her class.
I found the professor extremely unapproachable. Fairly easy to get an "A" though.
Best Professor I've had so far! Definitely take her 101 class! She's amazing! So clear on her expectations, and going over content, Love her!!!!

A really great teacher. She is interesting to listen to and holds your attention with her comedic personality. For a 101 class there is a lot of work but you learn a lot through all the work given. Overall a great experience being in her class.
So funny and hip

I am an all A student and put more time and effort into her class than all other class. Did all the work went to every class and still got a B. I had questions asked her personally and in emails and got short rude answers that didn't answer my questions. Lots of busy work. I had more work than my friend who's in a graduate school psych class.
Very funny! She was by far my favorite professor. Very easy to talk to and get along with.
Captive teaching style that keeps you engaged. The course work is a bit heavy. Overall a wonderful teacher.
Don't let the first few days of class scare you she really is incredible.

I loved this class!! I was somewhat interested in psychology before, but now love it and even changed my major. Dr. Henderson does make you work for your grade, but you can earn an A if you really try. It is a hard class and you learn a lot. Don't take it though as a bird course cause it's not, but it is entertaining and she's a great professor.

Attendance isn't mandatory but you'll need to attend class for participation points. She is easy to listen to and easy to follow. I'm a re-tred( this was my 3rd attempt at Psych, all from different professors). She sends a clear message the first two weeks of class. Keep up with the EASY work and you'll pass.
Extremely funny and made class interesting.  Applied subject matter to real world examples.  Attendance not mandatory but will definately help you in the long run.

If you are interested in learning, then this is a great class. It is important to be engaged and do the reading. It is important to attend class. Her teaching skills are exemplary and well thought out. She knows what she is doing.
Such an awesome class. Do the work and you'll do fine. Also, show up to class. The tests are half lecture based.

I did not learn much from the class. She got off topic quite often. I wouldn't recommend taking this course unless you absolutely have to. She makes it much more work than it is worth for a 101 class. If you need area 1 credits go take music, theater or sociology; don't take this.

This class was really easy. You have a ton of opportunities to get points. If you have never taken psychology before be sure to read some - the lectures are pretty good but i don't think you can get an A without reading at all. Very easy to pass but all the responsibility is on you - do your work and take notes!

Although she is very interesting to watch in lecture as all these ratings say, they are too immused to realize they aren't learning anything from the lecture that isn't in the book. She does a great job at using huge words that make sense to no one, and loves hearing herself talk. All TA's make her powerpoints - I think her teaching sucks

I LOVED this class. I learned a ton, and she's hilarious. Keeps you interested and intrigued. Lots of book use(weekly reading checks). Attendance is not mandatory, but there are always lecture questions on her tests and quizzes! Go to class and do your homework and you got this in the bag.

She is a really good professor, I currently have a high B in the class. You actually do need to read the book to do good in the class, but she is very clear with the concepts and it is easy to understand.

She is a great teacher her lectures are not mandatory but there are questions on the midterm and final from lecture. She makes you actually WANT to go to lecture she makes everyone in class laugh! She has strict deadlines but they are very reasonable. If you are taking Psych 101 take it from her!

Henderson is the worse professor I have ever had.  She is a pedant and loves hearing herself talk.  The work load is heavy, bordering on ridiculous.  For instance, I wrote a 6 page paper for apparently no reason. Se was supposed to give me feedback on it for a later paper but never did. It was infuriating.  She is a horrible, horrible professor.
Very good lectures, if you attend the lectures, take good notes and read the material you will do well.

She is an AWESOME teacher. She's hilarious and her lectures aren't mandatory but she is so funny that you actually want to go to them. You have to read the book but this class is pretty easy. If you're taking Psych 101 I would suggest having her. She's a great teacher!

I LOVED her lectures. I was always interested and learned tons of interesting things. She's hilarious and very knowledgeable. Be sure to READ YOUR BOOK and take notes. GO TO CLASS and actually pay attention in lecture and you'll be good.

She is very strict about dealines and due dates but they are all clearly posted on blackboard. Read the book and do every assignment. The midterm and final are hard easy if you do the work and study. Great Teacher!!

Dr. Henderson is a great Professor. I absolutely loved her lectures. Not only does she make lectures interesting, she will make you laugh. There was never a dull moment in that class. It's definitely not an easy class, but getting that A is very possible. You will need to READ THE CHAPTERS and ATTEND LECTURES. You will use the book often!!

Not an easy A class, but it is possible! Dr. Henderson is EXTREMELY wonderful at capturing students attention. If you want a good grade you have to be willing to study, read the book (skimming won't cut it), and attend every lecture! This class was unforgettable!

Dr Henderson is knowledgeable, animated, sassy & real. Prepare to work HARD. You must read the chapter every week, attend class, take LOTS of lecture notes (many ?'s on tests are from lecture) & self monitor your blackboard assignments.My one wish is she would let us print her slides so we could listen more to her lecture. Do yourself a favor & start/join an online/Facebook study group immediately!

Awesome teacher. Really teaches the content and really devoted to her field.I would recommend this class and professor to anyone who wants to know a little about themselves and psychology. Dr. Henderson will keep your attention, but you defiantly have to work for your grade.

I loved this class.  Dr. Henderson is a great teacher.  The class is not easy, but you really have to try.  This class is so much fun and Dr. Henderson makes it the best.  I love the class, and how Dr. Henderson teaches.  You will be so happy that you took her class.

This class requires a lot of work.  Go to class to get participation points.  At the end of the semester, she picks 4 participation days (25 pts. each) and there's your participation grade.  If you miss one day, you won't get the points.  READ THE TEXTBOOK.  She has reading checks every week for the chapter(s) read.

She's a hilarious proffessor and she makes you want to come to cass but this class is HARD to pass. I loved going to class and I loved her but I didn't even pass. There are reading checks every monday and class engagements wher eyuo have to go to class to know how to do. There's a lot of material and a lot to remember. The textbook is crucial.

Henderson is great. Her lectures are more than entertaining. Stay on top of Blackboard and all the assignments she assigns and you will do fine. Her exams are a little tough, but she is helpful. I would def recommend her.

Teacher is WOW! She really wants you to know your stuff like she does and her sense of humor is good. She assigns a lot of work, be prepared. She is confusing as she has everything due at different times of the week. Always stay on top of your blackboard!
I was a TA for Henderson's 101 class and it was really great. She just asked that you attend class and take notes to write the quiz questions. One meeting a week and then grading of assignments.

Dr. Henderson is an excellent professor.  I actually enjoyed going to her class.  Really funny stories and she is super passionate about what she teaches.  Her goal is to impact you in a positive way and change you for the better and she will! Yeah you have to pay attention in lecture, but that's easy because it's always interesting! Take her!

Professor Henderson is extremely entertaining! She has a lot of knowledge about psychology and is really interesting to listen to.  She always has fun stories to tell the class and it's the one class I never dread going to.  Go to lecture because there are lots of test questions based on it.  If you are offended by cussing don't take her class.

This was by far my favorite class of the semester. Dr. Henderson is a fantastic professor and she really knows what she is talking about. She is very clear about due dates and what is expected and the class really isn't difficult. The lectures were all very interesting and informative. She is amazing and I would take her class again in a heartbeat.

She was an amazing teacher, I loved coming to her class, but I had problems with getting the motivation to go. It feels like we don't cover much in the lectures and most of the information you get is from the textbook, but then you are tested on lecture based material. Confusing, but I loved her.
I LOVED this class, she's really funny and her classes are interesting and informative. her teaching style is fabulous. I would highly recommend taking this class!

OMG! Dr. Henderson is funny, engaging and informative.  Yes, she swears like a sailor, but she tells you upfront if you cant handle it...go someplace else for psyc.  If you cant hang, go someplace else.  She is an amazing teacher and if you step up and do the work she gives you all the tools you need to succeed. !!!!
Professor Henderson is so funny! She inputs stories from her own life into lessons and is very helpful when you ask questions.

Prof. Henderson is hysterical and super interesting to listen to. Always engages the class with funny stories and anecdotes. If you are offended easily, don't take her class; she cusses like a sailor and is very blunt.

Best Prof I have ever had! Extremely interesting class, and Dr. Herderson is very passionate about her subject. Completely inspired me. Make sure to read the book and attend all lectures, and you willl learn a ton!

Dr. Henderson is an o.k. teacher but I do have two complaints:  1)  she cusses like a sailor and 2) when discussing Asperger's Syndrome, she was very insensitive about it.  I have a close friend with AS and it was offensive to me.  She needs to  be aware of people's feelings.

Great teacher, Dr. Henderson is funny as h3ll!!!! Very fair and she has been my favorite teacher by far!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! If you pay attention and don't come to class to  surf Facebook then you will enjoy this class and do fine!! TAKE THIS CLASS!!!!!!
Prof is very funny, interesting, personable and hones/direct. Don't take this class if your lazy, or don't want to read.
Dr. H. CHANGED MY LIFE! She is hard, she takes you on a journey and at the end you will be a new and improved person. SHe is very engaging and lets her students fly.

She is very caring about her students and pretty funny as well. She always responds to emails and she makes the class requirements clear. You do have to do a lot of work on blackboard. You need to check it every day for class engagements and quizes.

Very engaging during lecture, and hilarious as well! Not an easy class--you need to do weekly quizzes and often times there is an essay to write. They are easy enough, but the points really add up, so DO THEM. Tests can be tricky, pay attention to statistics and facts about the disorders she talks about. Take good notes on the movies as well.

Dr.Henderson will change your life! She is such an amazing instructor, & she is super knowledgeable, she is GREAT at passing her knowledge onto her students. It is a class you must read for and participate daily. I HIGHLY recommend her!

Henderson is a bowl full of crazy, but the awesome kind.  Her class is fun to go to and always interesting.  She has no behavioral boundaries so don't take her class if you cant take a joke. If you don't like her, it is because you are too lazy to do the EASY work.  You can get an A if you just do the assignments.
Good professor. Doesnt give partial credit on the research which is ridiculous. Lots of busy work but you HAVE to do it to get a good grade.

Great teacher. Made going to class very fun! Lots of busy work, an assignment and 2 reading checks per week but the class was so much fun! She is hilarious! Warning: Don't forget to do the research. It's very easy...just do it...

This is not an easy class, lots of busy work and effort recquired to get a good grade. I loved going to lectures though. She made lecture fun, interesting, and relevant. If your willing to do the work I definately recomend because her lectures are really enjoyable. Blunt and sometimes crude tho, so don't take if you can't handle that
she is hilarious! beware she cusses a lot!! she does not care what comes out of her mouth. lots of busy work. the homework is soooo easy, but the tests are pretty hard!

Amazing Professor. She is hilarious and always has a good story for the class. The information is easy to learn and remember because she always has a good story to go along with it. I really enjoyed her class. Read the text and your fine! 50% of tests are lecture and other 50 is straight out of the book. Weekly reading checks & biweekly assignments

Very interesting, but also very hard! Professor Henderson challenges you and it's totally worth it! If you're the kind of person that actually likes getting something out of the class take her psych. class! If you just want an easy A DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS!

You suck at life if you don't get something positive out of her class. She goes out of her way to relate and keep things dynamic rather than monotonous and dry. She even helped point me in the right direction about an issue I've been having with my son at a time that I know she was very busy. Not everyone will do that.  Awesome professor!

She is great. She is very interesting and teaches a lot of real life stuff. She is very to the point and in your face. Her tests are open book-open note but the class is tough and you will earn the grade. You have to go to class or you will not to well on the tests. If you have to take Psych 101 get Henderson.
was entertaining and i was able to learn more life lessons then i was expecting when i first came in. great experience.

She is AWESOME!! I loved going to her class. Lecture is always interesting and she has so much love for psychology that you will love it too! Her tests and quizzes are not easy but not extremely difficult. Take the time and study and you will be fine! Do the work and you WILL get a good grade!! Definitely would love to take another class by her!

Interesting lecturer and gives easy assignments for easy points instead of just a bunch of tests. All tests are online except midterm and final. Going to class sometimes was pointless except to get the scarce notes down. If you read and know the book, you'll do fine. There are a few questions on tests you'll only get if you go to lecture.

Lecture is never boring. You learn more than what's presented in the textbook which is always a plus. You have to put forth effort so if you're looking for an easy A, don't take this class. Half the tests are based off lecture so you have to go.

Dr Henderson means well. Her lectures are funny and interesting but rarely relevant to the material. She tests over everything, including her personal examples & stories. Lots of little busy work. Reading checks due weekly. Assignments biweekly. Quizzes biweekly. Attendance and book are an absolute must if you want a good grade.

She really made me hate psychology. She was really rude when you talk to her, as well as you email her. Her attitude really pissed me off. Her office hour was useless. In class she never made things clear and you never know what will be in the test. You also have a lot of assignments. I put a lot effort in it but result was not good. DON'T TAKE her

Wow. I love psychology and she really made me hate it. I thought she was a great professor at first, really funny and all...but she doesnt work..at all. She has TAs do everything, down to writing tests that are HORRIBLE. Their grading isn't the best either. I didn't enjoy this class but put a lot of effort into it. STAY AWAY !

Spring will be different because people cheated on the online tests. I got an A on the final and the class, but you need to STUDY. Not one hour, but for a couple of weeks. Study your old quizzes and class notes, not much comes from book except definitions. Tests are partially written by TA's and are lecture based. She is an excellent instructor!
Love this teacher, would recommend to anyone that takes pysc 101!

Good intentions, decent content, but the quizzes/tests are atrocious.  Having attended every class and reading every chapter, I came out of the final with a D+ and absolutely zero feeling of personal guilt. I'm convinced no degree of studying could have prepared me for the unclear and ill conceived questions.

Best teacher I've ever had! Loved her! Great at making the info relative. She funny and down to earth. The class is exciting. Book is a must. Read every chapter and show up for class and you'll get an A. If you keep up its a cake walk!

LOVED HENDERSON! She was my favorite! I would definately take another class from here. You definately earn your grade in this class not an easy A but very interesting. Henderson is very fun and interesting but very strict on due dates. Great Professor!
She is a fun professor. She can be difficult and some things are stressful, but overall it's a good class and a lot of fun.

First week you'll feel like you are overwelmed, it is a demanding class. You MUST read weekly, and there are many assignments. However, she drops a test and quizes, and grades and a desent curve. Alot is required from you but doing it all it seemed to be easy to get a good grade. She does have an authoritative personality.

I did well in her class, but when it came to office hours she was very rude and closed- minded when it came to the questions I asked. I would not take her class again. During lecture she was funny, but only got through a few slides per class. I had to totally depend on the book because she never was very clear on what would be on the test.

She is hard, but she is such a dork, and super funny, She loves sex, and loves to talk about it.  She likes twilight, and she will tell you about it. But she is a great teacher and really helps you understand the subject.  Ask questions!

Great professor. She relates the subject to your life and has a great sense of humor. She is respectful of opinions but has a tendancy to be rude if she disagrees. She will not budge on her grading and she has no sympathy for slackers.

Henderson shows her worst the first 2 weeks.  She follows the syllabus to the T.  Very interesting.  Connects content to your own life.  Do the work and give them thoughts and the content will stick.  Doesn't take attendance yet you need to go to class.  50-60% of test questions come from lecture.  Sit behind the TAs (they write lecture questions).

great at returning emails, but snippety and rude replies.  i was excited to take the class and the info in the book was fascinating, but she sucked the excitement right out of me.  i couldn't wait for the class to be over.  take DETAILED notes on 1st movie she shows, b/c you will see questions on every exam on that movie.  AVOID if u can!
DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!! At least for 101....she says she is always willing to work with students however that is not the case. It is either her way or the highway....

Abnormal Psychology is finally a psych class filled with what you really want to know about psychology, and Dr. Henderson makes it very interesting and relevant.  She is a great instructor, and demands respect without always giving it in return.  Be prepared to be turning in a paper/assignment or taking a test or quiz weekly.  Not easy, but do-able
She is the bomb digity

This class is not hard, it just requires effort. I received an A in this class. This is my first semester of college after being out of school for 16 yrs. I have a husband and two kids to take care. If I can get an A in this class, anyone can. You just have to do the work. I also had 18 credits this semester. Dr Henderson is GREAT

Henderson, or Hooch as my friends and I call her, is not a very good professor whatsoever. Only half of the questions on the exams come from the text, the rest come from her lectures. And these lecture questions don't really have anything to do with the chapter at all. Don't take her. She cares more about cracking jokes than the students' success.

If you take from Henderson, don't let things get away from you, do your research hours as soon as you can, she gives out a lot of busy work, almost to the point it is annoying. She is entertaining, but at times can be over the top. She was very clever to give out course evaluations before you know exactly what your grade is. Go to class.

Unforunately, she did not have open book/open notes in my class, which made the tests pretty hard for multiple choice. As a lecturer she does a great job of keeping your attention and getting her point across. You earn your A in this class with the tests, but anyone complaining about it has no business in a 300 level class!

She was one of the greater professors i've had here at boise state! The class isn't easy, but if you study and read the book you'll be fine. tests are open book/note. she makes class fun and interesting, while still maintaining a professional atmosphere. I definitely recommend taking this class from her!

I just adored Kimberly Henderson.  She has a great personality and I really enjoyed her class.  She is very professional and entertaining at the same time while teaching a sensitive subject of abnormal psychology.  I really, really enjoyed her class!

she does not lecture from text but you are tested on her lecture, guest lecture, video, text and things she says we aren't going to cover. her attitude is that she's at that and then some. You as a student are wasting her time and have no knowledge whatsoever concerning anything. She is vulgar and leud on occassion. she isn't interested in students

Ok you all giving a woman crap for doing her job is a buch of crap. She rocks anf or those of you who think she is stuck up you have never actually talked to her. maybe you should look at yourself when you think of your grade insted of blaming the prof!!!!

Professor Henderson is fun, engaging, and knows what she's talking about. Her class is fairly easy, with all tests and quizzes being open note. I would not hesitate to recommend her to another student.

Professor Henderson is what every professor should be like. Her class is not the easiest class ever, but far from the hardest. She definitely set the bar high for professors in my college experience. She is fun to listen to and makes the subject very relateable. You won't regret taking Psych101 from Henderson!

Prof. Henderson is hilarious in class, engaging, lenient to an extent, and her class is relatively easy with open book tests and quizzes (except for the final). If you have to talk to her, though: be afraid. She's abrasive even in email. Pay close attention to the online calendar and check Bb EVERY day. She won't break policy to help you.

Her lectures are entertaining, but her quizzes and tests are ridiculous. The questions and answers are very poorly worded, making it difficult the know which answer to choose. 50% of the quiz and test questions come from lecture, but it's often difficult to know which lecture comments you'll be tested on. I would not recommend this professor.

Simply amazing, Never has a teacher shocked me as much as Henderson. She is fun, engaging, and really makes it a point to listen to and help her students. low class work, a weekly quiz, and biweekly tests. all you have to do to pass this class is attend lecture and study lightly. I highly recommend Prof. Henderson

Dr. Henderson is an awesome professor, if you go to class the material will be pretty easy because she makes it very memorable. I took her class Fall 2009, our quizzes and tests were at home, so open book, open note. Our final is comprehensive and it will be open note with a small BSU blue book. I HIGHLY recommend this class, it's very interesting.

Professor Henderson is wonderful. She cracks me up and is able to relate to her students quite easily. Her tests are slightly hard, but if you STUDY and KNOW your material, then it's really not too hard. Quizzes are open book, and you get 10 minutes! PLENTY OF TIME! Fun lectures. She's understanding and hilarious. Very abrasive teaching method ;)
I do not like this proffesor she is not approachable at all. She says that she will help you but she never does.
Dr. Henderson is SO COOL. How dare you people give her an average rating.

Favorite teacher ever! I love this class! It can be kind of hard if you don't keep up but it is very interesting and she can keep your attention whether you sit in the front or the back. Definitely recommend this class to anyone. I will be taking more classes offered by her.

This class was alright. The prof can be pretty funny, but uses very profane language at times. She also doesn't follow the material in the book either, which makes it hard to know what to study. Easy assignments, timed open book tests, really not that hard of a class.

Henderson is EXTREMELY difficult.  I took her class in the spring of 2008, and at that time there were no open-book tests.  She must have changed the way she teaches her class when she found out half of the students failed.  Quizes over 40 page chapters and one journal entry for each unit.  I WOULD NOT reccommend Henderson.
Very engaging. Assignments require work, but she's totally willing to work with students in order to see them succeed.

she is one of the best professors here. I loved this class she knows how to make it interesting her test and quizzes are not too hard you do have to study. do not expect an easy A but you are able to get one if you work at it. I got C's on all of my test except one and the final and I got an A... she is funny and helpful always answers emails :]
She is awesome!

I was kind of surprised to read the comments about how hard the tests and quizzes are... both are open book and open note and I haven't found any very hard at all.  If you come to class and remember to keep on top of the quizzes, tests, and class engagements, you should be fine. She's entertaining to listen to, but just manage your time well.
Great - fun to listen to
This professor is the bomb shiznit. She has figured out how to use blackboard for our advantage.

I took 101 as an online class and Prof. Henderson was fantastic!  She shows a genuine interest in how her students are doing in the class and if you miss an assignment she follows up with you to find out why.  I ended up missing three journal assignments which cost me my A, but that was entirely on me.  She's an EXCELLENT professor!

This class was really hard. If you take it be prepared to spend more time on this one than most. The teacher is not that bad in lecture, she keeps it interesting. But, the tests and reading suck! did not expect a subject that I really like to bring me a C!

Henderson is amazing. Very personable yet professional. You get as much out of the class as you wish to, but she'll push you. You'll laugh, you'll cry, you might walk out. She may offend you at some point. haha. It's not an easy grade. But if you work for it you'll be rewarded greatly, I still take what I've learned from this class and applied it t

n opportunity to have another class taught by dr. henderson. she was an awesome teacher and i would recommend it to anyone who is willing to work a little bit, and isn't lazy & enjoys learning new things. Her lectures were never boring.

Dr Henderson was an awesome teacher. The class was difficult, but it's psychology so it's going to be. I'm an average B student and got a 86% in the class. It takes effort to study for this class but she's very nice, intelligent and helpful. If you do service learning from her, it makes it even better. I loved taking it from her, and hope to have a
She is a very bad instructor, she is out to just collect a pay check. I can't believe the President of the University would allow her to instuct.
I had no problems with this professor and I am not even a Psych major. A lot of whining going on here. She is not easy, but that is the way it is supposed to be.

the hardest core class i have taken so far. tests are super hard. reading assignments are around 40 pages. you have to work hard to get a good grade. (lectures generally aren't boring though) if you are really interested in psychology then take this class, if not, avoid at all costs.
Trust me. You do not want to take Dr. Henderson. Just trust me. Take her if you like, but you will wish you hadn't. Very unprofesional for a professor.

DO NOT take psyc from Henderson! She does not teach at a 101 level. Her tests are extremely difficult. Tests are based on lecture plus any videos she shows. Just taking notes doesn't cut it. You have to study  constantly for this class if you want to pass. Quizzes over 40 page chapters is required. Also, one research paper is required as well.

I have been on the deans list four semesters in a row. By taking this class i recieved my first C. I feel that this instructor is useless. She is good about anwsering her E mails but this does not make up for her lazyness. She makes the Hardest test I have ever taken. DO NOT TAKE THIS TEACHER!!

Her quizzes are very hard. There is a lot of reading so be prepared to spend lots of time each week with your book.  Her lectures are very interesting and she makes them fun.  She is very strict about late work so don't plan on even doing it if your aren't going to get it in on time.  Her tests are HARD!! A student getting a C on the tests. CRAZY!!

She is a very difficult professor. You have to read 40 page chapters in the book and take quizzes on them. She uses powerpoint, but goes through the slides so fast. Instead of going back to a certain slide, she tells you they are on blackboard and you can go there to get the notes you missed.  I would not reccommend her at all!
She is awesome and always has great stories!!!! I wish she taught other subjects too!!!

I am a 4.0 student.I had to drop this one! Way too much work.2 chapters to memorize each week(80 pages),plus 2 quizzes/wk.Lectures come after quizzes and tests are complete?!I would have recieved a C and suffered other course if I stayed past the 3rd week!Quizzes & tests have technical applied questions even though you get no lecture before hand.

Had her class for the first few days. TERRIBLE professor. She is very unclear about her quizes and puts everything on Blackboard. LAZY. Inconsistent. DO NOT take this class if you want a professor that is there to teach, or should I say do their job.
Her class is fun and she always has great lectures.  Her tests and quizzes can be hard and are very poorly worded.  If you know how she thinks you'll be great!
She has good stories just dont ask questions in class, she will tear you appart
inconsistent and does not announce quizes. do not recommen
Loved the class, loved her.  Very fair on grading, very helpful.  Overall great class, would take from her again.
You definately earn your grade with this prof. She is extermely helpful and does her best to be useful for the students. Does get off topic easily but her lectures are always worth going to to.

Very inconsistent, and can be unreasonable.  If some of the class does bad on something, she punishes the whole class by changing the way she grades everyone's papers(weekly journals), rather than just giving the slackers a bad grade. I don't recommend taking her class.

cool/interesting class. online quizzes can be taken multiple times, so easy 100%. tests could match lecture a bit better, but follow her study guides and you'll be fine. the many online quizzes cushioned me from any bad test grades. one pg final paper so easy! do the experiments EARLY though!!!!

Kim is a great teacher, very nice and approachable. The class is easy enough. There are online quizzes for every chapter, four tests and either experiments or a paper. The only problem I had with her was at the end, she entered the wrong quiz grade and penalized my paper for being late, when I had proof that it wasn't. I still ended up with an A.

I was excited to take this cool Machine Learning class and it quickly became my least favorite class of college. Dr. Qu himself is actually quite nice, but he doesn't really know what he is doing and could not explain concepts well. In order to succeed, you have to start working on assignments super early and go ask questions in-person.
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Tough grader

comment: The list is too long to put here, avoid at all costs.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read

comment: There are 10 question homework almost every week. Three midterms were easy and copies of homework questions. However, final was very hard. But, he seems to grade on a reasonable curve.

One of the worst lecturers I've ever had to sit through for a semester.  I'm sure he's a brilliant mathematician, but he should not be teaching. The lectures are torture! Hard to follow what he is talking about, and does not explain the concepts very well. Avoid him if you can, you may pass but you won't learn much.

Prof Qu was helpful enough the few times I asked him about homework problems. Class was a little on the hard side and I think he spent a little more time on the proofs rather than on clarifying concepts. Does have somewhat of an accent which takes some time to get used to. A good instructor overall so long as you do your part and study for class.

Fun class discussions analyzing pieces of art and literature and relating them to the history. There is a group project at the end, but it is very easy even with a dysfunctional groups. Collects notecards instead of reading quizzes so you don't have to memorize the text. Very clear on what is expected on the test and I never got less than 101.5%.

Awesome teacher, for what I thought would be an awfully boring class, this turned out very interesting.  Do the work and you'll be fine.  take notes on each reading, useful for the tests.  no tricks, all straight forward.  so glad I took it.

Christy has turned out to be one of the best engish instructors ive had.She is very helpful with papers,generating creativity, and is extremly knowledgeable.There is alot of writing in this class and research work,but she helps out and makes it a good learning experience.Not a great public speaker.says um ALOT.kinda funny.great teacher!take her!

Daily readings required and quizzes over them. She is very hard for an intro class. Exams are very hard. They cover lots of info and large sections of the text. Must identify many artworks. A group presentation is also required. Doesn't seem to know what she's talking about. Good idea to take Art 100 prior to taking this class. NOT RECCOMMENDED!
She's great-keeps things exciting and fun. Grades very fairly.

Ms. Vance is extremely helpful when it comes to your writing. She always has suggestions to what you can do to improve. Be prepared to do quite a bit of writing. Almost every class, you'll have a writing assignment due plus mandatory papers. The papers are easy if you enjoy writing research papers and you get the chance to rewrite them. Recommend!!

She is a great English teacher! Write three or four essays, then did a computer/video project on one of the essays. Some of the in-class activities are pretty pointless...but English has always been easy for me. Very nice and willing to help. Always recognizes me outside of class and says hello. Even wrote me a letter of recommendation!
Christy Vance is a great teacher to take english with
Good teacher.  Be prepared to do a great deal of writing.

Great prof and I learned a lot! Be sure to show up and take good notes. The tests are mult choice, short answer, and essay. They can be tricky but if you actually do the reading all the info is right there! Really easy going guy but makes you know your stuff

Great professor! This class was very interesting and we had some great discussions. Eric is a public defender, so he has plenty of entertaining anecdotes that are relevant to the topics of conversation. He likes to play Devil's advocate, which is great to get you thinking. I loved this class!

Eric is not the hardest prof but is definitely not the easiest. his questions are pretty hard and the main way to pass is by doing a good paper. his questions are very practial and concern everyday life

I really enjoyed this class.  Learned a lot.  Fair with his grading.  He answers you questions and makes the class fun.  Can't tell his political view point.  That's how it should be.  He plays both sides very well.  Nice guy and won't keep you there all night.
this teacher is pretty practial. public defender and is right to the point. hard to tell if liberal or conservative. you better read the book or you will fail
Outstanding instructor!  I hope to take him for another class soon.  He has a wealth of knowledge and challenges the students to discuss and defend their position.
super easy and fun. If you show up to class, you will do just fine.

Take this class with this prof if you want an easy A and an easy time in class. He doesn't always know what he's doing, but he eventually gets to the point. You have a worksheet due every class but you usually don't have to turn it in, just sign your name on a sheet and put your grade down (even though it's never actually graded). Easy online HW.

Steve is easily the best 160 teacher. His lectures are straight and to the point. He knows this class is extremely difficult, so he is an easy grader. If you show effort on the tests he will give you SO MUCH partial credit. His lectures can be boring, but its Math 160 so of course it's going to be boring. He is the reason I was able to get an A.

Chamberlain is not a bad teacher, not an amazing teacher. His lectures are actually helpful if you are caught up on homework and take good notes. If you are confused though, I recommend just going to the tutor center or his office hours for extra help.

Steve is easy going and pretty relaxed & I think he's the guy to take.  It is important going into the class that you understand math 160 is not easy. Every topic builds on each other so if you don't understand it, get help. If you do every assignment, attend the majority of the lectures, and get help when you need it, you will pass math 160.

Steve is awesome. Look, math160/170 is HARD. Don't expect any professor to just magically make it seem like basic arithmetic. Steve was great about adjusting homework due dates if necessary and also slowed down if people weren't grasping a concept. There's a ton of material to cover so just be prepared to settle in and work hard and you'll be fine.

Good Prof. Lecture was sometimes dry and a bit confusing at times, but he gets you through the class, and will keep re-working problems until you understand it if you ask. If you really want help, go to his office hours before class, and he gives great one-on-one help. Would have liked it if he went more in-depth with some concepts.

I would take math from Steve, based on what I've heard about other math professors.  He's such a nice guy, never has a problem explaining something again or going over questions.  All the homework was online, which I liked. I was so nervous for this class, but I'm making it through really great!

Steve explains concepts with the expectation that you understand algebra intimately. If you ask him to slow it down, he has no problem; Don't be afraid to say something. Steve was very helpful in explaining concepts I didn't understand as well as showing different ways to complete problems. Good teacher, students seem uninterested, enjoy it!

He is a good teacher, but he doesn't answer questions well. I only made it through this class because I did all of the homework and the extra credit reviews. If you don't study you can probably get a C in his class, but some of the tests are brutal
very helpful and did an example of all the poblems, go thru many new concepts quickly, enough that refreshing on earlier concepts helps on test.

Mr. Chamberlain is extremely helpful and works through everything in great detail. He is always willing to stay after class to help anyone with questions and always has a good attitude. The tests are difficult but he does a review session the day before the tests. Do the homework and you will pass the test.
Good enough guy, tough class unless you have a solid foundation in math.  I did all the homework and studied for his tests, he is quite challenging.
Good enough guy, tough class unless you have a solid foundation in math.

This class moves very quickly. Homework is due every day and you learn a new lesson every day. If you show up and do the work, you'll be fine. The tests are easy and he reviews the day before. If you speak up, he'll help you. He is a bit awkward and scattered but he knows math well and does his best to help.

He teaches the material well, but it is extremely boring. The class is very easy to pass. I attended less than half the time and easily got an A. If you're good in math and are looking for an easy A without having to show up too often, take his class.

I found Professor Chamberlain to be a bit dry in his lecture style, but he is extremely helpful during his office hours and he only goes as fast as the slowest student, as long as you speak up if you have any trouble with something.
good professor, half homework online half in class, gives review sheets which are super helpful. Tests are totally straightforward

Horrible. I took calculus in high school and managed to get a C in his college algebra class. Handwriting was horrible. He'd be doing problems on the board, get halfway through, realize he was doing it wrong, then start all over. Talked monotone and slow. Homework due every class. Tests were average. Ended up retaking this class from a diff prof

Teachers is boring but is very clear in lectures and gets concepts across well.  The homework is generally harder than it needs to be which is frustrating, but tests are much easier and he gives great reviews.
I'm not sure what he's getting at by being monotoned. He's really boring and doesn't care about his students

She is definitely not good at explaining, most of what i actually understood was from the textbook. Her tests are hard. But at least she offers some extra credit. To get in class participation she uses another account for questions from the material during class. I do not recommend taking her if want to get a good grade.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: She is the worst professor I've had. She is very hard to understand and is not clear when teaching lecutre. She does not post grades anywhere,  you have to figure it out for yourself. She doesn't not let you see the correct answers on quizzes after so you are on your own to figure out what you "think" you got wrong. All tests are in testing center.

Would not recommend Zeynep. Her tests are very difficult, her lectures are hard to understand, she doesn't post your actual grade in the class anywhere so you have to try and calculate it on your own, and compared to any of the other economics 202 professors her class is much much more challenging. Oh and the homework is very time consuming.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY

comment: Don't get me wrong, Zeynep Hansen is very nice and very passionate about her area of expertise. However, she is very hard to understand and is not good at explaining the material. She uses LaunchPad for her online homework, which crashes about twice a week. Her lectures are important for attendance, but you don't learn almost anything from them.

Professor Hansen is passionate about her subject and it shows by making a boring class a little more interesting. She grades for attendance, so show up. Homework: not bad at all, and material pretty easy to understand if you just read a little. Reading is short too. There are some tests throughout the semester, so that's a bit of a pain.
ratingTags: Respected--Participation matters--Caring

comment: Dr. Hansen was very helpful and gave off a vibe that she wants students to learn and be successful. Material was challenging, but interesting, so it made learning engaging. My biggest complaint would be that in most cases, she is slow to grade the coursework.
One of my favorite teachers I've had. Interesting lectures, particularly if you keep up on the readings of which there are a lot. Very smart, and you'll learn a lot.
Does not understand student life. Not a great teacher and is focused on only herself and not actually teaching her students. Strongly discourage taking class with her.

She is very interested in the subject she is teaching. Always open to discuss material and assignments. The test is essay so if you can read and write that's a plus. It's not an easy A, but you might just learn something.

Good teacher, you just need to attend lecture and pay attention. She goes over everything you need to know, and will go over it as many times as needed. Subject and teaching style is a little dry, so it is hard to keep focus and pay attention. Tests are very tricky! She does curve the tests and gives out extra credit, so that helps.

A good indicator of how well the teacher is, if you can read the book and get out of it just as much as when she explains it, she's probably pretty bad.  Uses questions from the book, which are ridiculously worded.  Class test averages are well in the the low 70's high 60's.  HIGHLY Do not recommend.  Nice person, just terrible teacher.

Her tests are a little tricky but in the end she dropped a lot of the scores and kept only the higher ones. She is very helpful and if you email her or ask a question she will take her time to help you. She seemed a tough teacher in the beginning but got a lot easier towards the end. If you want to learn economics, definitely take her!

I was in the same section with the previous two reviews and couldn't disagree more.  She is one of the few professors that actually uses the board to demonstrate concepts instead of premade PowerPoint slides.  She always asks for questions, and if you don't ask any then why would you expect answers!

Not a good teacher. No prepared materials for the class. No structure. Not easy to understand. Didn't provide test reviews. Tests never made any sense and didn't coincide with the material we were learning. Very unorganized and felt like my summer tuition would have done more if I had gone to a bar or burned it. AVOID THIS TEACHER if you can

Would not recommend her at all. Wouldn't even suggest that she teach in Public Education. There was no structure or preparation for the course done on her part. Everything was thrown together as she went and very hard to understand due to her strong Turkish accent. 3 days before the final she tells us she hasn't ever taught the course before.

I thought she was a wonderful professor.  Even in a large class, she strove to make important concepts understood.  If you have a problem with accents, she may not be the prof for you. I plan to take 201 from her as well, if it's available.
Worst class I've ever taken in four years. she is nice but difficult to understand. Too many readings are assigned. Have no idea what to study for for the tests. Don't ever take this class

Sometimes difficult to understand.  Hard to please with written assignments, there was never a clear understanding of what she wanted.  Tests were just memorization of three or four long academic journal articles with very little actual economics.  Way more analysis of methods and not nearly enough actual useful information.

Hard to understand and not helpful at all. Plus she is not very organized and can easily lose your term papers. Class would have been better from a professor who could get points across, where as she expected us to know stuff a Nobel Peace Prize winner had taught her.

Don't be scared of taking her because of her first name! Great teacher. Always asking if you have questions and never wants you to not understand. Lectures are the best way to understand the text. So read and go to class. Tests are tricky but understand definitions and concepts by heart, you'll do real good. Always available to talk in her office.
Economic History Thought: Her multiple choice questions are hard, it's very difficult to distinguish the right answer from given possible answers because possible answers are  similar to each other.
How is she hot?! She is hard to understand and does not understand that some of us have jobs and not all the time in the world to read worthless things. I have no idea what to study.

Not a huge fan at first but realized it gave me a better perspective of Social Problems from the view of other students.  I loved this class! She gave great feedback and was very quick to respond to emails.  She's big on citing and referencing.
Awesome class!  Kimberly keeps it interesting through out the semester.  She is very clear on the requirements.  I would definitely take another class from her!!!

Kim is an AWESOME professor!!  She engages the class, and pushes the students to do their best.  If you do not pass her class... you are not trying!  Her tests are from the text, class time required group discussions and presentations, and she was willing to work around my work/family schedule to accommodate missed class time.  Highly recommend!!

Overall the class is fairly straight forward and the assignments are pretty easy to do. But, she is such a hard grader. She is soo picky about your assignments and how you do them. I really enjoyed Kimberly's class. It was not an easy class and I appreciate that! I didn't pay to go to school to learn nothing. Kimberly challenges you to explore the material and doesn't just give out good grades. You earn them. I would recommend Kimberly's class and feel like I really learned a lot from her. Thanks Kimberly!!!

Kimberly wants things done EXACTLY how she sees it. Everything is SO meticulously outlined, you're bound to miss a point or two on many things. I wouldn't say she's a bad instructor, I'd say that she doesn't understand what a true teacher is. I had a cum. gpa of 3.88 before her. Needless to say, I won't be taking a class from her again.
Reasonable and easy to deal with. I definitely recommend her for SOC 230. She has an interesting point of view and keeps class progressing at a perfect pace.

Loved this class! She is tough, but fair. I took it online, weekly discussion boards, and a few papers here and there. midterm and final were hard, but i did well on the papers and discussion boards so it can make up for those. highly recommend her. very nice and responses to you quickly.
A really good instructor.  Quick to return feedback and uses rubrics so you know what is expected.  She understands students and wants them to learn.  Took SOC 230 from her and learned a lot.

She was a great instructor.  In my three years as a student I found this one of the better courses I have taken.  She isn't big on tests but uses a lot of written papers so be prepared to do some work in this class

Professor Johanek is an extremely easier teacher. She grades things really easy. Took the class online and it was the easiest class ever. One assignment due each week. Kim is great, she is always willing to help, if you have questions and email her she will answer that same day.  Scores are posted in blackboard and prompt. Kim is amazing! she will help you in anything at all and is always willing to find examples for you to relate what we are learning to pop culture. Excellent! (Wish I could give more than one chili pepper!)

comment: I took this class online and it was awesome! She can meet up with you easily to go over assignments. Quiz almost every week, and the quizzes are pretty hard. The weekly assignments are pretty easy. Total time per week was about 2-3 hours. Would love to take her again!
She's good.

Excellent!

Excellent lecturer with good examples.

she is a very clear and helpful teacher, it is not mandatory to go to class but you kinda have to due to the in class work and quizzes. expect a lot of work but she helps you out.

He likes  to use slides and his slides are pretty good.  He is pretty funny! though he is a bit shy.  I would take his classes again any time!

it is amazing teacher !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
