It's not mandatory to attend class but she does use a clicker, which is participation points. Not a very good professor if you struggle with chemistry.

I also have an A in this class but she is one of the worst teachers. She takes no time in preparing a lecture and she herself doesn't understand the material. If you take this class you will be reading the book cover to cover to be able to understand.

Pretty easy class. Don't worry about what the other people have said on here. It's Chemistry, and Chemistry is hard. You can't expect to learn it from the teacher exclusively, you must read the book.I currently have a 4.0 in this class. She has been very lenient with due dates and I feel that she is more than competent to answer my questions.

This class is stupid! She reads powerpoints word for word, and she didnt even make the powerpoint, i havent learned anything new from her,  Horrible at answering questions, does not keep you interested in the material, goes through material so fast you dont know what just happened!

DO NOT TAKE CHEM 111 WITH HER!  All she does is read Powerpoint presentations in class that she didn't put together.  Horrible at answering questions, an entire class petitioned to have her removed.  Hands down, one of the WORST professors I've ever had.
Tests were short and easy. They are multiple choice, however, so you can sink or swim.

Dr. Hannah was a great professor. You can tell she loves the subject and knows her stuff. Fairly easy class, especially if you go to lecture. She is always willing to help students out. My only complaint is that she is unorganized. Grades take a long time to be put in to blackboard and it is hard to follow her syllabus schedule.

I do not recommend taking Dr. Hannah's class.  The instruction was very unclear, to the point that a bunch of extra credit was given at the end of the semester.  Her grading, or that of her TA's, is not consistent from one assignment to the next.  There was no feedback given on assignments.

Dr. Hannah is a lousy instructor.  She is not organized at all.  She uses TA's for all grading, which is fine if you keep them all on the same page, but she didn't.  There was almost 0 feedback on assignments/quizzes.  When I sent her an email with my concerns, I got a passive/aggressive response.  I would not recommend taking her class.

Dr. Hannah seems like a very genuine and great person...outside of class. I've taken her for pathophysiology and now I'm taking her for epi. I've noticed both her classes are completely disorganized. Also, we've had 4 lectures already cancelled and it's barely past mid-semester. Easy A class but not worth the $1,000 you're paying for to be there.

Professor was not helpful. Never responded to emails. Not clear in assignments. 4 syllabus changes. Lecture class cancelled without notice multiple times. 3 times different professors had to fill in. Assignment due dates changed multiple times. Always on the date they were supposed to be turned in.

I recommend this professor for anyone needing to take patho.  Yes, the class is a lot of work, but it's expected for a 4 credit class.  I recommend just reading the chapters and completing all assignments.  This combined with a little bit of effort will guarantee an A in the class.

She is a difficult professor, many students do not like her because she forces you to do all the work on your own and she expects excellence and professionalism. If you want an easy class, do not take her. If you want to learn how to be independent competitive in the real world, take her.

First, grading is not clear, each person has their own total point. Secondly, If  She favors someone (classmate sat around me, we all share the essay to see), she grades very generous .  If not, she grades very hard. For example, in research essay she said" minor error", but she subtracts %25 grading,..2 prof in class, Dr. L.Tengelsen is easier...

He seems fun and acts like a nice guy until your final portfolio and he just screws you over for no reason. Lead to believe I would do well and now it is too late to do anything, and I have been left in the dark
ratingTags: GROUP PROJECTS

comment: His teaching style is not for everyone, but I really loved my honors English class! He was very interested in the "why" of writing, more so than the "what" and "how". He really made me think about the purpose of writing and how it really is an art form. He requires participation from his students, but the work load is less than I expected.

Bruce is always willing to take time and talk to you about course material, writing, or anything English-related. He's warm and welcoming and genuinely interested in helping his students succeed. He's an authority in the field of the personal essay and freshman composition, yet is down-to-earth. A real resource and asset to BSU.

I took the Radio Essay course from Bruce. I learned a lot about creative nonfiction, and learned new ways to approach writing, to revise, and how to just get interested in my own work. He relies on students to drive discussions and be interactive as opposed to lecturing all class. I highly recommend this professor.

Ballenger is intelligent and passionate about his craft.  However, he doesn't give a RIP about his students.  Queries are passed to a TA that's inaccessible.  Comments regarding the work you submit is limited and generally unhelpful. He seems to be more concerned with his lecture circuit then his classrooms.

Very great professor who is interested in writing and the success of his students. He knows his craft well and cares about the writing of each student. Really great professor! Take his class if you want to improve your writing.

I would recommend this class and Dr. Ballenger to anyone. I learned SO MUCH from him! He is smart and really cares about writing and teaching writing. This class requires a big time commitment, but is worth it in the end. Dr Ballenger is fun, engaging, and showed me how to think about writing in a completely new, fresh way. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!

Bruce is an amazing teacher. He cares about he students and the work but he's doesn't coddle anyone. If you're going to work with Bruce put on your big boy pants and be prepared to work. I've learned more about writing and teaching about Bruce than any other teacher on campus. And it was never easy.

When I took Theory of Rhetoric and Comp from Bruce, I thought he was an amazing professor. But when I took E524, Creative Nonfiction Workshop, I realized how out of touch he is. He cares nothing for the students and I watched him "bury" a grad student because Bruce was offended by what they wrote in class.

Word on the street from a graduate in Rhetoric & Composition-Bruce is Bruce and teaches every class the same way.  It?s true and this past year he displayed little interest for the writing produced in this graduate level course. There?s nothing more disappointing for a student writer than having a professor give you the impression he doesn?t care.
An amazing professor who both cares about material and his students.  He requires a committment, but really makes it worth your while.  A gem in the English department.

This was my 2nd time taking this class and I must say I enjoyed it the 2nd time around!  Colin made the class enjoyable! Yes he did go off on tangents but that's what made the class.  I would highly recommend the class to everyone!  Do the homework & turn it in when it's due.  Tests were not cumulative & he had an 8% extra credit assignment.

Colin is a really cool, laid back guy who has a real passion for math. He goes off on crazy tangents often, but that's what keeps his classes entertaining. He genuinely wants his students to succeed and his tests and homework aren't that difficult if you somewhat pay attention. Highly recommended!

This man is goofy and spacy. However, he will stay late, come in early and help you understand the material. Homework counts for a lot so do it. Test can be hard but he will reward you points for effort. Do any extra credit, it will help you at the end.It was great taking his class, I enjoyed it and would take another class from him :)
Great professor. He is very helpful and his classes are very clear. Easily the best math professor at BSU.

I failed this class twice before taking it from Colin. He really wants to make sure every last person understands. He is not a mathematician like all those tenured guys. He explained math for people that struggle with it. You will never hear "Because that's just how you do it" from him. I got a B! Great choice for fans of Tara Sheenan.

Well, he does a good job explaining. A little spacy but a good professor too. Not fond of how he grades, but gives a lot of partial credit. Hard to tell what's on exams. BUT it is also a hard class on it's own. Their are other more straightforward professors but he's a nice guy and easy to work with. With all math, it's all about what you put in.

Professor Rainford changed my perception of society.  I was not a social work major when I took his class but now I am enrolling in the program.  He changed my life..the first teacher who really ever made a difference in my life

Will is a very interesting professor. He has some great stories. He can be kind of an ass, but it's pretty funny actually. He is very smart and is there to help you. Just show up to class and you will be good. You really only get tested on 3 novels that you read, your community hours and attendance.
The most egotisical man. He's has a typical law enforcer mentality. Class was easy but If I can help it I will never have to be around him again. Annoying!
Very smart man but he is so involved in other work and research he has little time to put into teaching

will is by far one of the most helpful and intelligent professors that i have ever had. as long as you contribute to class discussions and pay attention youre golden. there are no written exams just opinion based responses on material. TAKE THIS CLASS!!

Dr. Payne is approachable but unorganized.  The syllabus was put on Bb on Mon for T/TH classes. PDFs in lieu of text. Class was monopolized by 3 students.  We often only had 20-30 min of tchg out of 90.  Held writing conferences with 3 students in her office twice during semester.  Her comments proved helpful when I was able to obtain resources

The text book she used was horribly vague. A large volume of research papers were assigned. Students formed groups weekly to review each others's drafts. No tests, just research papers... lots of them. Lectures were somewhat monotone. Wasn't the fun class I anticipated it to be.

This professor was extremely difficult to please!  She would look for the most minute details to subtract points.  She would require about 3 posts a week and also require 2 responses for each post.  I felt like I was making up responses because I was being forced to respond.  This class was by no means enjoyable when  it should have been!

She was very flustered and often late. Grades were never updated and she generally just seemed like she didn't care or know what she was doing. I honestly dont think I learned a thing. She is a nice person but a horrible teacher.

A little disorganized, but a lot of fun. She will drive students who are anal retentive nuts, but she is willing to listen and when the class has an issue she will work it out. The final project was a blast and pretty unique. Kind of a goofy teacher but definitely cares about her students.

Mrs. Jones seems flustered and unprepared. She seems like she's making up lesson plans on the fly. Constantly spells things wrong on the board in terrible handwriting. She often speaks in incomplete thoughts/sentences. I would definitely not take her after knowing her style.
Teaches communications but really isn't great at communicating herself. Seemed flustered and unprepared often. Definitely participate because if she knows you, she'll bump your grade

I like Steph's teaching style. She is on the student's level and doesn't act like she owns the communication world. I enjoyed hearing her take on things. It's not hard to get an A or B in her class. Do the work and study for quizzes. Be sure you have internet access because she uses Blackboard.

For a communication class, she is the worst communicator. Her tests aren't based on the book or the notes, more of her ideas and the wording is terrible. There is a lot of inconsistancey in the class. Only one personal speech and one group speech the whole semester. Several essays and many little time consuming assignments. Don't take her!

She is a horrible teacher. She makes up her own words and spelled everything wrong. She never told you what to study for the tests and even if you studied from the textbook, nothing was on the test! I would not take her!!

I enjoyed Mrs. Jones class, as she stated in class this was the first time the comm dept. used the textbook and the first time she used blackboard.I could tell she had alot of passion for her subject. The class I had her in she was fun, engaging, and willing to listen to differences of opinion.

This class only had two speeches (one was a group speech) and two tests. She practically handed out the speech grades, which was nice. I got 100% on both of the speeches, and they hardly met any of the requirements. In the end, I'm glad I took her, just because it was so easy.

Im pretty sure I knew more about comm. than she did! she read straight from the textbook and misspelled words and made words up. She agrees with everything you say pretty much. She has weekly quizzes on blackboard. I haven't learned one thing. DONT TAKE HER!

For someone who teaches Communications, she sure is horrible at doing it herself. Often loses her place in lecture, stutters, paces, is late to her own class, MISSPELLS EVERYTHING, and always takes her bad mood out on the class. She botches her own quizzes, and won't give you credit unless you notice. Avoid taking her, I wish I did.
He left after a few weeks. Bad experience during that time, I don't know if he's still teaching. Not a good time.

Way too much material covered in the most dry, uninteresting way possible. Had the annoying habit of saying he would let us go and then keeping us there for another half hour or so. He LOST our tests, blamed us and then made us retake them. And I have never wasted so much paper as I did with all the printing of readings and assignments required.
Tim was a great instructor!  He really wanted to connect with each student.  He is easy going, just don't take advantage of him.  He truly cares about you!

Excellent class despite condensed 3 week. He's fun and engaging. Grade heavily weighted toward online chapter reviews.  Just do them, and you're good. An exam each week but not cumulative; lots of multiple choice, and each has 2 short essays.  Study guide provided. Just pay attention, study a bit, do online chapter reviews, and you'll get an A.

There's a lot of reading and writing for an intro class and the professor is not clear on expectations. Though he is nice and genuinely entertaining at times, I wouldn't take this or any class from him, given the choice.

This class is very easy.  All the homework is easy to get done during the lecture if you bring your laptop.  Going to class is not mandatory but he gives a worth-while bonus to the students who do show up.  He also has a sense of humor and it is easy to tell that he enjoys what he does.
Very helpful. He knows we all have lives outside of class. Assigns a lot of work but is easy if you follow instructions. Easy A. Hillarious and genuinely caring person. Highly recommended for a 101.

Assigns way too much for a 101 class. And tests are hardly weighted. Don't really have to attend lectures. Connect assignments are really important and take a lot of time. Wish I would've known that he assigned so much junk.

easy class which you never have to show up for except for test days. Do the connect assignments and study the key terms and get an easy A he was a fun teacher never to serious tells alot of fat jokes i had a great time.

This class is pretty simple if you do what the prof tells you. It's basic stuff, study the terms on the study guide provided and get an A. He's a nice guy and funny but the lectures are pretty boring. It would be a ton better if he would keep the student comments to a minimum to shorten the length of class time.

He has a sense of humor which made going to the classes more enjoyable. but at the same time felt kinda pointless being there. he puts his notes online. he doesn't even like teaching 101 so it wasn't very interesting when talking about certain topics. not terrible but not fantastic.

This is such an easy class. Buy the book and get extra credit for staying after the tests. Really easy A. Not a great teacher but what can you expect from a core class. I recommend it if you are just filling a core.

Fun, informed, great personality! The best thing about this professor is that he adores the field in which he works. Also, he is a human being, with understanding and compassion for people who don't necessarily fit into a box.

Going to class isn't necessary. Slides are online and he reads directly off of them and cracks jokes. Nice guy, but pretty boring class. He'll work with you on anything. He has a full time job outside of teaching so he understands we're all busy with other things. Easy papers and hands out review sheets for exactly what's on test. Easy A.

His lectures (which are posted on blackboard) are straight from the book.  He reads straight from the slides and has boring stories that are completely inappropriate and any GOOD counselor should know not to push the boundaries on client confidentiality.  Basically, show up (he gives 10-15 pts e.c), possibly read, and you'll be golden.

gave out lots of extra credit for showing up. i liked that a lot because i think it means something if you show up every week cause i dont do too well on tests. i liked him a lot, his lectures were very clear.

he is an excellent teacher, he gives out plenty of extra credit. His tests are sometimes difficult but the essays he assigns are always 100%. he understands that you have other classes too. i strongly recommend him.

alright the comment below this comment is crazy. really clark posts all his power points on black board so u really only need to go to class on test/quiz days. there is a study book that you can buy with the book DO IT. i have an A just from that book. He is really funny and makes u laugh, understands that it is an area class and doesnt expect much

Completely worthless. The material he lectures on does not fit with tests. He trails off frequently and then runs through power point slides to quickly. Overall scoring system for the class is completely ridiculous. Don't take him if not necessary.

My class is on monday nights from 6-9. The class is long, but he keeps my attention and makes the class enjoyable. The tests are based on the textbook despite what the syllabus says. He gives a lot of extra credit for people who stay the entire class. He allows for interaction, which can suck when people treat it like a psych session. Great teacher

He is a very busy person, but still somehow manages to grade 300 papers on learning methods. He uses personal examples in lectures, however tests come from the book. So you gotta use that and the study guide if you want to excel. KNOW YOUR VOCABULARY
One of BSU's best!  Clear and easy to understand.  Don't let him catch you texting though!

Jim is a great teacher. He is easy to understand and going to class was a pleasure. He was very funny and very tall! He was EXTREMELY passionate about the subject which made it that much more interesting. Highly recommended area class.
Jim Langley is entertaining, funny and engaging. It was a joy to come to class, and I was very sorry to see the semester end. Top scores all around. He is a gem.
One of the best teachers I have had at Boise State. He is hilarious. Stay awake and study for tests and it should be a problem.

Jim's a good prof. kinda goofy sense of humor. easy class (this was the honors section) one group project over one of 6 plays read over the year. attend 2 bsu productions. tests easy if you go to class.
This was an easy A.  Go to lecture, sit thru the slides, participate in mini-real-world-scenario-skits, and you will get an A.  Some math, but not too difficult.  Overall, I liked this class
No Comments

What a waste of time. Upper div course that is taught at a grade school level. Learned absolutely nothing new, but still spent hours every week on busy work. She obviously likes her job and helping students, which is the only plus.
Had this as an online class and never have been so overloaded with busy work before. The work is easy but she piles it on.
Drink tons of coffee because this is the most boring class on campus.  It's taught at a 6th grade level.  Too bad I'll never get those Thursday evenings back...what a waste of time.
Fantastic professor.  Truly cares about her students and it really shows.  Is willing to do whatever it takes to help them succeed which is what is needed for a degree like general studies.
Nice and helpful.  She personally helped me get my AA degree core certified with registration who previously denied it.  Easy class if you do the work
Kind of rude, doesn't act like she really wants to be there.

It's not necessarily an easy class, but if you do the work, it can be a solid A.  Test are hard if you do not study and take all three pretests.  But there are no surprises, consistent due dates, and answers to the Mid-Term and Final are given in the pretests.  She is not out to "trick you" like some professors--she is clear and concise.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Clear grading criteria--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Does not grade discussion board posts fairly or consistently as she has her teaching assistants do it. Takes several weeks to return grades and then gives zero feedback on how to improve for the next assignments. Does not return emails or respond to questions posted in discussion boards.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters

comment: Lots of information, tried to engage everyone, unique course. Made my first exposure to international worthwhile.

So she is really nice. Be prepared for a PowerPoint enema. Slides will be so numerous, and crammed with information you'll need time at home to see them all. Grading, ha, what grading. The teachers get so backed up they just gave everyone attendance and case study points. Wonder why she took roll or why I attended class.
Great class, great instructor. Looking for more classes she teaches!

Dr MTB has to be one of the most loved professors at COBE. I'm not an IB major, but wanted to be after having her for a class just hoping some of her coolness and smartness would rub off. In the next lifetime.

Glad I had Dr. Black before graduating.  She obviously loves her job and wants the best for her students, which makes it hard not to care too.  Super busy, but always seemed to make the time for me. One of the professors I will remember the most for sure.
Really great professor. genuinely cares about her students and makes class interesting. 2 thumbs up!
Dr. MTB is inspiring to be around and genuinely cares about her students. Great professor and helped me view my education and experience at COBE in more positive way.

Very passionate teacher.She has very good ideas but does not lecture that much. She has expectations that the students will lead the discussion. She wants students to have a real world expierence in her class which is good.Did not give prompt feed back on assignments and struggled with hybrid portion of class. Wonderful ideas needs focus on a few.

One of my favorite profs for sure. Dr. Black expects alot but is fair about it. I would take another one of her classes but am graduating and she seems to only be teaching IB320 now and another one with her husband I heard was really good.
Hybrid course so more assignments and fewer class lectures so makes you learn  material. She gives lots of feedback. Got a lot out of the class. would recommend.

Very knowledgeable and super passionate instructor, lots of interesting projects and assignments, brought in guest speakers and had us meet with companies which was cool.  I actually felt like I was being prepared for the real world.

She is very knowledgable. She knows a lot and is almost to eccentric about it. She never really conveyed her expectations until after an assignment was turned in. It is a lot of work, but not too hard if you put forth an honest effort.

Pretty lax at grading...only have to show up once a week plus 2 test days...no structure to the class...will actually get angry if you ask questions she doesnt want to answer...unclear about expectations...there is a large workload...would suggest against taking this class from her

She is very excited about teaching International Business.  The workload of this class is insane!  It should be a 4 credit class.  Weekly quiz, 2+ page papers due weekly, required weekly reading of the entire Economist & then must post 3 blog style entries, a 10 page country analysis, an interview and report of an international business, huge tests
She is hot but boring. She was less prepared for class than I usually was. Not a great professor but an easy one.

1 on-call assignment, 2 multiple choice exams (easy A if you do study guide), 1 interview assignment, participation.  These are the only grades given for the entire semester.  She's not bad in lecture, but you can tell that she'd rather be somewhere else.  Very hard to get a hold of.  Inflexible her for demands. $150 textbook, but you'll use it.
She is hot, her class was easy, she was very helpful. I would recommend this teacher to anyone.

Such an unclear class. Bought a 200 buck book and struggled to make sense of her lectures just to find out that the questions on the study guide are identical to the test. Incredibly smart but doesn't know how to "dumb" down her lessons for the average person, only teaches 1 out of the 2 days a week, and doesn't even administer her own tests.

You must read the book before you come to class. Her lectures can be confusing and she sometimes goes off on tangents. You must study hard for her exams. Part of the exams are essay questions. She provides a study review guide. She is funny and overall a good teacher. She does offer participation points so go to class.

Very nice professor but not clear at all. Tried very hard to follow her lectures and even followed with the book but could never comprehend her teachings. Studying very hard for the tests was the only way to do well.
Scattered but very focused on trying to make sure people understand

Completely unorganized, whole class was essentiallt two presentations, and expectations on them were not clear even after asking her many questions.  No real textbook, and what is given does not have to be read.  After the class was over, I was completely confused about what I was supposed to have learned.  Very easy grader, however.

She is a ok teacher, but if you want structure, she is not the one.  Very disorganized and pretty much wings it as she goes.  Depends on the class discussion to keep it moving, which was lame, because I didn't pay to hear what the other students have to say, I pay to learn about Business.
Lots of rabbit trails in lectures, which can be quite dull and painfully long.  However, the class is very easy and if you know the definitions in the book, the tests will give you no problem.
I found the class extremly educational.  Meridith added humor to the class.  Her objectives were clearly laid out.  I would recommend her to anyone and I would take her class again.

I liked her, she was nice and helpful. There are 5 exams plus a final. If you know the vocab and print out her slides you will do great. One project which requires you to read a case study and answer qustions no presentation. Very Easy. I would take her again
She is not too hard but sometimes certain test questions can be tricky.  All multiple choice, alot goes off vocab from chapter

A really great proffesor. I was very nervous taking this as a summer course, but fortunately I was lucky enough to be taught by an interesting, comical teacher. Lecture is not boring if you just listen to how excited he is over the subject. Great proffesor and I recommend him to anyone.

I absolutely HATE speech, I went into Ross' class dreading it.But it turned out to be my FAVORITE class of all time! Hes hilarious! gives you powerpoints that are accessible on blackboard.The tests are cake.the speeches are relaxed and fun. :] i would HIGHLY recommend taking a class from him. Only 4 exams a few small projects and speeches.VERY FUN!
Makes you work for your grade, never learned as much in a 101 class as I did in his.  Great teacher if you're there to learn but not an easy A.  I would recommend him, worth the money!

Robert is a pretty good teacher. His class was fun to go to because we usually did group activities. He's young and was cool. He's a tough grader considering it was a 100 level class. I put forth A effort and Got a B. I'd recommend him for any one who has to take COMM 101.
Made learning fun!! Still have to do the work, but we always had a good time in class. Comfortable environment for discussions and so forth. Would definetly recommend.
Pretty cool and fun teacher. Have to work very hard to keep a good grade in class. Not the type of class to get an easy A in, but keeps the serious level lower than a lot of other classes.

This class wasn't that hard as long as you paid attention. Definitely not one you could sleep through, but still a fun class. Great guy, pretty good teacher, worth your time but not the class to go in if your looking for an easy A.
Prof. Ross makes you work hard for your grade.
Easiest professor ever! No need to show up for class, simply read the book and ask friends when the tests and quizzes are. He reads directly from the book.

Professor Cluphf may struggle through slides a bit, however his personal stories have complete relevance with the subject matter. He is a fabulous instructor. He is knowledgable, and more than willing to help you with questions, or work with you if you are doing poorly in the class and have an interest to improve. Great class, easy A if you read.

An embarrassment to the university. He is a nice guy but is not even a decent teacher. Swears a lot to get a rise out of class. Likes to tell personal stories that have nothing to do with the topic. Stumbles through reading his slides. Would not take him!

Alright, here's the deal. It's a 100 class, so it isn't super entertaining. BUT, he is a good professor and he is VERY passionate about his subject! If you just go and talk to him he will be MORE than willing to help you! He is a very nice guy, and he really wants you to learn and he wants you to enjoy class.

The topic of the class is not my fav in CJ- pretty boring. And I don't think that Dr. Cluphf made it more interesting. The tests are pretty easy and require little effort but lecture is really boring.
Enjoyed the class. No homework, just three straight test and the final.  Extra option available. Read the material and you will do fine.

I've taken him for more than 1 class and he's way cool. Always willing to work with students and do whatever needs to be done to keep the subject interesting. One of my favorite teachers. I'd certainly take him again if he taught another class I needed. I learned a lot with him teaching.
Very nice guy. Tests were really simple and easy. His power points got boring about half way through semester but he was able to keep class interesting by having great class conversations.

This man is frustrating. Nice guy.. but he shouldn't be teaching ANY sort of Criminal Justice class. He reads off his bland slides (inefficiently, he needs to take a refresher on how to read). He makes this class irritating! Just attend the review day and tests and you'll pass.

He is a very good professor. Knows his information well, and makes the class fun. Not sure why people are saying he doesn't know what he is talking about. He doesn't make the tests too hard, just study a little bit and you will be fine!

Good professor - will take him again - don't believe the negative comments here.  He's a good prof. clear, consise, and willing to work with you if you ask for help.  Attend lectures and read the book and you'll do fine.

Pretty good guy for CJ 101. Knows what he's talking about. Uses several examples in his lectures to get students to understand what's in the powerpoints. Can be boring at times, but can also be funny at other times. Recommended if you are looking for an AREA I core course.

This is by far one of the worst professor I have had. He has admitted that he has been stopped for DUI and was let go. He also admits to having cigars (possibly Cubans) in his car when traveling back from Mexico. Does not know the material as he has no practical experience beyond textbooks. Never in the trenches. All information is from the book.
good class

I would also like to add that if you attend class, read and study, you will succeed. As in most all classes, book material and lecture will be in exams. We, as students, are responsible knowing all information!! I and others have taken several classes from Prof. Cluphf.

I disagree with the negative posts regarding this class. The information presented in class was informative and the exams were fair. I also believe the preceeding posts were certain from spiteful individuals who received low exam scores because they were ill prepared for class and most likely failed exams due to lack of good study skills.

This guy should not be teaching a mandatory upper division class. When asked about the answers to test questions, he didn't know and all his lectures have little to do with what's actually on the test. Avoid him if at all possible.

Nice guy, but all he does is go over the summary of the chapters and has the class IRAC the cases.  He is not the most prepared instructor and his speaking ability needs work.  His tests are questionable, since what he covers in class has little to do with the material on the test.  I won't take him again for a class.

I WAS looking forward to this class so much... I was so disappointed with this instructor. He has little field experience it seems and just reads to you out of the book. If you ask questions, he doesn't provide insight. He often gives wrong info and doesn't correct it. Great if you like learning from slides... not me though.
good professor very straight forward and fair. teaches right out of the book so if you read the book and show up a few days to ask questions you should do fine. tests are a little tough.
Great professor. Learned a lot from this class. Gives lots of examples and is very fair when he grades.
No Comments
She's really hard to understand. Lots of quizzes, so you have to attend. Confusing on due dates and what she is or isn't going to collect and grade.

He's really affable and interesting, and he actively wants to help you. The class was a huge waste of time, but he made it as interesting as he could. A little bit of group work and very little assigned, but he's strict about grading. Completion of homework is more important than perfection.

comment: Mac is awesome! He's got tons of life experience and really wants us all to succeed and enjoy our time in university. Great resource for questions regarding anything English-related. You can tell he really loves what he does. Pretty in-touch with himself and his class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Amazing lectures

comment: UF 100 Story Science Fiction was one of the easiest classes I've ever taken. Attendance was mandatory in the discussion group, but not in Lecture. Mac Test didn't care if students were distracted during his lecture, he would just keep talking until the time was up. I used Lecture time to do homework for other classes.

Mac is wonderful professor I've taken for three courses now from 200-300 levels. He is smart, easy going, and makes the material funinteresting. In class quizzes are a breeze. Read the materials, participate in discussion, show up, and think in depth about what he's trying to say and you'll have an A. Also very, VERY easy on the eyes.

I had Mac for UF 100 (Story) and he was hands down my favorite teacher. Very energized and made class laid back. He knew it was a class no one wanted to take so he didn't shove it down your throat. I plan on taking more English classes with him in the future.
Mac is very entertaining and very easy to get along with. Super witty and makes class interesting. UF 100 is a joke but an easy A if you do the work. Who doesn't want an easy elective.
This is the stupidest class ever. There is a lot of pointless discussion in class over books. At the end of the year a group documentary is due. Try for a different UF theme.
Awesome Professor! I would recommend him to anyone and everyone! Two papers, three tests, three quizzes. Go to class for notes and you will know everything you need to pass!!!
Very helpful and understanding. Grades fairly and has reasonable tests. Very kind and a good lecturer who is able to make the subject interesting. One of the best professors I've had.
I would recommend this teacher to anyone! He has an animated voice that really keeps the class engaged. He knows his stuff and how to keep it interesting.

This is the second class I have had with Mac and both have been a pleasant experience. He is fair in his testing and makes all forms of literature interesting. He's helpful, understanding and obviously knows what he's talking about.

Absolutely the best teacher I've ever had.  Mac keeps it light and interesting.  He treats all of his students like adults, and expects us to act as such.  There was a lot reading, but it was pretty interesting stuff.  "cultural exchange in transatlantic literature" sounds awful.  It has been my favorite class because of Mac.
Best professor I've ever had!

I can't get enough of this class.  Mac makes a subject that could easily be dreadfully boring interesting and fun.  The lectures are fun, and he's ridiculously cute and brilliant.  Attendance in lectures is not taken, but is taken in discussion group.  Much of the tests and quizzes are from his lectures.  Lots of reading required.

Great prof! Very fair and helpful, in/outside of class. Cares about his students. Brilliant. Passionate. Makes learning easy and fun. Great lecturer. Will work with students individually if needed. You will learn a lot from his classes. One of the best profs the Engl Dept has to offer!

Mac is an awesome professor.  He is interesting, knowledgeable, and makes learning fun. He is charismatic and enjoys teaching and sharing information. He values his students' opinions, thoughts, and ideas. He truly wants his students to learn and enjoy their time in his classroom. He is very flexible and fair. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!
awesome teacher! very clear and makes class enjoyable. he is extremely knowledgable in the subject which makes it easy to learn. take him if possible!!

Professor Test is very charismatic, a story-teller, and witty. He makes the class interesting and I dare say enjoyable. He gives students an opportunity for extra credit and allows creative options on major papers. Quizzes often. The class was organized and structured very well. Uses a variety of teaching approaches. Excellent. Would highly recomme

Mac is a great professor! Interesting lectures-he's incredibly knowledgeable.  He's a pretty harsh grader on papers (but it IS a Lit class), & quizzes were a bit tough, but overall the class was enjoyable.  He's also VERY available via email and during office hours & enjoys student feedback. He really wants students to succeed!  Highly recommended!
Rediculous excuse for a teacher. Online class, I knew more Chinese than she new English,  gives you impossible time restrictions on quizes and tests

Awesome teacher, very friendly and jokes around alot. Harsh grader, but that can help to perfect the language. With work, the class is not hard, but can be with slacking off and not going to class. Great teacher!
A few of us are studying for a test tonight and thought we'd post here. Yeah, it's a good class. Take philosophy 101 and you'll learn alot. The tests are straightforward and the lectures are clear.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: She was a great teacher! I had to retake this class because I did quite poorly the first go around with a different teacher. However this time, I felt like everything was so easy to understand and she was very responsive when I needed help.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--Caring

comment: Prof Erin is excellent. Enough said.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Caring

comment: This was one of my last classes for my major. I enjoyed all the ethics topics and learned a lot. My field is healthcare and I will be able to take alot of the concepts with me into the job. The instructor was fair and the text was awesome. Take her if you can.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: This was my first online class and Prof Erin has it on point. I took this class in the summer so it was very fast paced homework due every few days. Graded on chapter quizzes, db posts, group project, midterm, and a final. Its not too bad as long as you put the work in.
Be ready to work hard and have a very open mind. The class is all about critical thinking and exploring your own beliefs.

It was a challenge but it was an amazing class with an amazing instructor.  She is an asset the school.  Dr. Anchustegui does not want you to regurgitate facts.  You are encouraged to learn the material so that you can think for yourself and come to the right conclusion.

Professor Anchustegui has the 100% Online experience nailed. Hard to imagine Philosophy in that forum but she makes it work. You will read a LOT and write a fair amount. She expects above average writing skills and participation in BB discussion groups is a must. Tests are challenging but are based on material provided. I would take her again.
Great professor that went out of her way to help when I didn't understand something or I was struggling with something.

Philosophy is a hard subject in general but overall I hated this class. Towards the end of the semester the lectures were long and boring. She takes attendance and gives credit for attendance at the end of the semester. Quizzes are given every week as well as homework. If you can take this class with another professor I would recommend it.

This class is almost over and frankly it was a good class. It was better than I expected. I had heard of philosophy being hard and the teachers not caring, but this was not the case. Take this course if you don't mind doing a lot of reading.
This class was not hard but it was a lot of work. You have to read the textbook. Prof. A's teaching was good, the powerpoints help. Make sure you follow the instructions and you will do fine.

The only reason I took this course was it satisfied a "DLL" and was online.  Liberal Arts are vapid and useless.  However, Erin was an awesome instructor.  I have had questions at 4 on a Saturday afternoon.  I received an answer 15 minutes later.  Mostly I received an answer within 24 hrs.  She is very helpful and cares about her students' success.

I took the class thinking it was going to be like other classes. It covered a lot of topics and we went quickly through the last module. It's better than some phil courses I took at BSU. A lot of work.

Pretty easy A. teacher was quite unorganized and scattered. Assignment due dates and requirements were usually unclear. 2 essays, quite a few quizzes and questions from the book. I prefer classes that require less effort. Note taking was pointless, just read from the book. Sent around a sign in sheet at beginning of each class and assigned seats?

Took this class my first semester of college and have mixed feelings about it. Philosophy is very confusing but she understood this. Most of the class was repetitive. Make sure you get the book and go to class if you want a decent grade. Her final was tough because all the other tests were incredibly easy, bu then come the final she changed it.

This was a challenging class and we covered alot of environmental issues. Ithought it would be more political, but it wasn't. It was pretty balanced. The text was ok but the course supps were better. All in all, it was a good course. Recomended

I loved this class, there were only about 7 modules in the class and she made them due every other week, because she knew that most people have other more important classes. You actually have to do what she tells you though, the readings were pretty boring but the videos and other things were interesting. Do the work and its an easy A.
Very helpful and always available to meet during office hours or at Einstein's. She grades papers pretty easy, in my opinion. Her tests are easy.  She really knows her stuff.

This class was hard. he is a very dedicated professor..although her teaching may be a bit fast, she gives you lots of opportunities improve your grade i would recommend going to class everyday, because you get very behind on discussion if you miss class.

I thought the class itself was really interesting and intellectually challenging. However, Erin was not what I expected. Prior to this course I had heard many good things. In actuality, she was hard to get a hold of for help and she was constantly accusing people of plagiarism. I had to dumb down my work in order to pass.
I think this class will be useful someday. I don't know when. But I enjoyed it and the tests were fair. I liked all of the assignments and stuff we did in class.
Erin is really cool! She is incredibly smart and really knows her stuff, but is generally understanding when students don't quite get it.

This class is fine and you don't even have to read the bok much because there are so many aids on Blackboard. The lectures are easy to follow just make sure you keep up with the assignments and quizzes. Regular quizzes can be a bummer, but they help you keep up. Recommended and you'll like philosophy

Some of the concepts are difficult to grasp at first, and I appreciated the professor's willingness to review them at the start of the next class. Highly recommended. The study question assignments were useful and the in class assignments too. Recommended.

Clear in defining the theories presented in the readings. The class uses essays that allows you to fully develop ideas. Engaging material. Philosophy wasn't a focus of mine, but this class was highly enjoyable.

Good professor. Makes lectures interesting with her examples and really explains the material well. Even if you aren't that good at philosophy, you can get a good grade. If you study the midterm is easy
Extremely wonderful instructor and truly cares about her students. Because of her, I found a love for Philosophy that did not exist before.

AMAZINGLY excellent teacher. tells you everything that is going to be on tests, and you just have to study it. Go to class and participate in discussion, read your book when she assigns it, and you'll get at least a B
super cool teacher and has the students interests at heart. always willing to explain anything and answer any questions.
Horrible Teacher.  Goes on rants about being an adjunct teacher.
This was no fluff course and it was fun. Highly recommended.
I really liked this class over the summer. it was fun and challenging. i really suggest taking this instructor she made the class fun and i learned a lot.
She is a very nice and helpful professor. She seems to love the field of work she is in.

The logic class I took over the summer was a small class. The material was kind of boring. The class was taught pretty well considering what I expected. I really tink this class is important if you go to law school but too bad bsu isn't teaching it anymore. The teacher seemed to really like students.

I took her online class this summer. The class was easy even though there was a lot ofreadin. The videos were long. I liked the module on personal identity. The tests were really good and I thought the grading fair. I would definitely recommend this prof.

On a good day, I wouldn't be able to think of something positsive to say about this professor. I took the class online and got an A with little effort so I guess she's easy. She was unhelpful, inconsistent in grading, unclear in assignment requirements, unskilled in using a computer, and unwilling to acknowledge her mistakes? Avoid if possible.

She was a good teacher and explained things pretty well. You should definitely attend in order to do well, and pay attention to the lectures. Sometimes students were rude, but she handled it good. I liked the class. The best professor I ever had my entire college career!

She was extremely passionate about philosophy, and you could tell that she wanted her students to be too. She takes plenty of time in class to answer questions and re explain difficult concepts, as long as you ask her to. She's also extremely cute. I was too afraid to ask her to go out for a beer, but she told the class she would if we asked.
I love this class and the teacher makes everything very clear. I think everyone should have to take this class for there major because its so valuable.
I enjoyed this class and learned a lot about philosophy. I think that the tests were a little hard, and the grading could be clearer. But overall, it was a good class.
I really enjoyed this class. The lectures were interesting and the tests were about the material we covered. I would definitely recommend this class to other students.

This professor was funny and made class as interesting as possible! I'm looking forward to her next class. She gives all the questions on the test, a week before so you can study and know the question. All tests are essay and mainly if you show up to class it's not that difficult! she offers extra credit too!
Nice but not always clear on when things were due.

The test questions are often worded in a very strange way, with a lot of negative words. E.g. "not". It makes some of the questions really confusing, thereby causing students to select the wrong answers when they know the correct ones.
Hated the course content but the Prof made the class bearable!

I took this course online during summer. It would have been an easy A had I done all the assignments. I slipped towards the end because, hey, it's summer. I have things to do. All we did was read some articles, look at some powerpoints, and post to the discussion board. Nothing thrilling or exciting. Easy A if you want/need it.

A syllabus that outlines the class, including test dates and assignment due dates would be extremely helpful, especially when trying to time manage with an online class.  Expectations were not clear at the beginning.

Ughh... Well, all I have to say is that if you want to receive the easiest 3 credits in your life, then take phil 101 in the summer from Dr. Anchustegui.  I didn't learn much but it was the easiest A I have ever received.  I've taken online classes at the local community college that were exponentially harder than this class.

Terrible online instructor. She didn't actually do any teaching but instead tested us over the reading (unlike other online professors). It was difficult to contact her. How she graded the tests were inconsistent with previous tests without warning. I felt like she didn't care about the class. Only take this professor if there are no other options.
Logic is a somewhat difficult subject, but Anchustigie works at the class' pace. She is very helpful if you ask for help. There isn't much of a schedule, but I would recommend showing up to class.
awesome!

She's nice and helpful, a bit confusing, i got an A+ on 2 of 3 tests, went to class, did well on my work. Somehow I still got a B? Didn't make any sense. So always make sure you know your grade.no schedule, she does whatever whenever
Erin is a great professor, makes things really easy to understand, will push back hw and tests if people aren't understanding the topic.
Great professor! You'll love the class!
She was very clear and took time with the students. I had no trouble getting emails from her. Her lectures were great and she followed the syllabus. I really liked ethics.
AMAZING TEACHER! So nice, and very helpful. Material was very interesting, and the class was VERY easy. Even though attendance is mandatory, you will want to come to class.

One of the worst classes I took at BSU.  She was totally disorganized, never (ever!) responded to email from anyone.  Lectures were convoluted and confusing, and she often repeated herself and then skipped over things we were supposed to know.  Didn't follow syllabus, tests were graded quite harshly.  AVOID!!!!!!
I took this class online. She was one of the most unorganized professors I have ever had. Maybe she is different in the classroom but online, I would NOT take Philosophy from her.
no comment
No comment
I like this teachers lecture style. She explains things very clear and takes time with students.
This professor didn't teach PHIL 201 last semester.
Horrible teacher! Very boring in class. Doesn't explain things well.

I took her class over the summer and she is very insightful and she knows what she is talking about. she is very helpful and always willing to help out... it is a hard class it is a lot to ubderstand in 5 weeks. she makes a very hard subject as clear as she possibly can.
Nice teacher. Lectures good and I had to think a lot in this class.
No Comments
Went mostly by the book.  Lots of review time, which was extremely helpful.
Truly wants her students to do well.
very helpful in teaching
Good class, good professor, very clear
Cool prof
She tried her best to be clear in her explanations. She does a good job of explaining things several times so everyone gets the information.
She was so great, one of the best profs ever!
Very good and clear
Good teacher. She was nice. Helpful.

Philosophy is one of those subjects where you either get it or you don't I think.  I understood most of it pretty easily, but she would slow down if anyone didn't get it.  She's pretty cool about grading too.
I loved this course, and her deliberate and methodical way of teaching. She's so great, I really recommend her to anyone whos had a hard time with philosophy.
No Comments
She was a nice lady and tried to make everything as clear as she could
No Comments

MGMT301 is not an easy class and taking it online was not a good idea! you have two exams which are not that hard, there is a lot of reading you have to do, quizzes questions are straight from the reading. However the group project is hard, OMG!! people won't do their work and won't communicate with you, and you can't do anything about it.
Instead of Blackboard tests, he assigns papers. I thought they were easy. There are group projects which are hard to do with an online class.

He said he doesn't care about how long your answers are, but he does. If you think 10 pages is long enough, make it 20. If you hate group projects, stay away. I honestly don't how group projects can help anyone become a better leader because it doesn't.

I loved this class!!! You must attend classes, but the lectures are easy to follow along with and there are usually assignments to help you understand the concept better. This was the first class I ever got 100% on a test! Study the Powerpoints and you're good to go! Also, be prepared to spend a lot of time going group work and a group presentation

This was easily the hardest class I have ever taken. The material itself is not so hard, but considering 90% of the points for this class are based off of writing, it made it difficult because he is a very tough grader. I would never recommend taking this class from him online.
Funny, entertaining, engaging, dramatic, easiest college course I've ever taken. By far my favorite class ever. Teacher reminds me of Santa Claus. Loved it!
Difficult to get an A in this class. He is a hard grader and expects you to go far beyond his written requirements. Material is easy though and quizzes aren't to bad.

Everybody complaining here must have taken the online version, because I had him from 6-9 on Wednesdays and his class was great and not too hard.  Sure, it was difficult to get A's on everything, but it's like that in most 300 level classes.  He's a really nice guy who kept you interested even during the boring stuff.  Take him in person instead.

I took his class online and I hated it.The material is not hard but the amount of work is huge and the grading is tough and not too fair.There are weekly mandatory discussions,I missed one discussion(that unfortunately to me consisted of 2 parts)and that lowered my participation grade from A to D:0 I heard it's easier to take it in person

Hard to take interest in this course. His study guides pretty much cover everything that WILL NOT be on the tests. He takes roll but attendance is not required to pass. Tests are 40% multiple choice, 40% fill in the blank, 10% essay. Don't buy the book. Slides have all the test questions.
Took it online. Do the work and you will be okay. Hard grader. Easy B, Hard A. Great course material!
This class was online and required a lot of reading. There was weekly discussion posts, 2 essay exams, and 3 projects. This class requires a lot of time but the material is very easy. I got an A.

Loved this class in English 101. She gave clear direction and helps you to understand your writing better. If you do your homework you are going to pass.

comment: mrs Packard is an amazing teacher and genuinely kind, reading and small essay each week, 3 big essays. and 2 of those will be used for your portfolio.

comment: Mrs Packard is so cool and nice please get her as a teacher

comment: Professor Packard without a doubt is the most amazing English teacher I've ever had, as a student who has always struggled with english she is always there hands on to help you whenever. I would HIGHLY recommend her she's extremely helpful!!

comment: Probably one of the most kind and genuine people I've ever met. Packard is an amazing teacher and and even better person! I wouldn't take 102 from anybody else if I had to do it over again.

comment: Prof. Packard is one of the only professors I've had that really cares about what your writing about. She gives amazing feedback and truly tries to help you as much as possible. This class though was a lot of work compared to all the other 102 classes. The good thing though is it is very organized so you won't fall behind.

Professor Packard is honestly one of the best teachers I've ever had! Her class is so simple as long as you do the work and actually go to class. If you go talk to her about your paper, she gives great ideas and helps a ton! Having the book for 101 is key, but 102, not so much because pretty much all the readings are online. Definitely take her!

She was fantastic. Any time I had concerns or questions, she was there to answer them, and she was extremely helpful. As long as you help yourself in this class and email her when you miss days or if you need help, you'll do well. At the end of the semester she said if we ever needed her for ANYTHING, her door was open. I respect her for it.

Danielle is a great teacher. I am not a huge writer, & she was ok with that. She will go out of her way for her students, & truly cares about their grade. She is a tough grader, but you can always go back and revise your assignments. She counts attendance as points as well. A lot of the work in done in class & you get to work in groups a lot. TAKE!

I had her for both English 101 and 102, and she is awesome! She has everything laid out for you and is super helpful, and very flexible with students. If you do everything she asks of you, you are most likely going to receive an A.

Great teacher who really cares about not only your grade but preparing you for future english classes. For most of the papers she walks you through every step of the way and as long as you meet the requirements you get an A. The way she teaches class makes you very involved and close with one another. MY best college class yet!

Loved Professor Packard. She really cared about each student. She knew everyone by name and could always tell what everyone's individual projects were. I always felt comfortable asking questions. Fun class with a great teacher. I hate english but golly she made me understand and get an A. I had a about 5 absences and still did okay.

She was a great professor. Really cared about how her students did. She also really knew that English 101 is meant to be a basic class and treated it as such, while this is true, you will notice improvements in your writing. Very easy to pass the class and you will get to meet a great person along the way.
Wonderful teacher who really cares about you as a student. She will take the time to help you develop your unique voice and style. If you want to grow, take a class from her.

Danielle was a wonderful teacher.  Very clear, very fun.  Always willing to help if you just made even the slightest effort to get any kind of assistance.  Very active even for an early morning class which helped start the day proper.
she is not clear at all in her lacturs. i extremlly regret takin class with her. i dont recomnded her

Loved Danielle, She was very helpful and passionate about teaching. She wants every student to succeed. I really appreciated her handwork and willingness to help each individual in her class. Neat Gal, I bet you would enjoy her class.

Very nice and helpful teacher. Easy to pass her class as long as u try. If u at least try you are guaranteed at least a B in the class. You has high energy all the time and is very understanding. I recomend this teacher to all.

She is a great professor. She's extremely helpful, I was kind of nervous to take this class, because i dont like english much, but she explaind everything so well that it made it easy. I passed her class with an A. She's easy to get along with and I would defenitely recommend her.
overall a great professor. she is very easy to get along with and very helpful. great class and i recommend her.

Awesome professor!!!
Knowledge, experience and caring,

This is obviously a fun class and Carla Jean is a wonderful lady. She has a quiz and a written final but they are just to get you to read, she went over both of them after we completed them. If you wanna learn the correct way to play pool or just want to have fun take this class!
No late work accepted, not even with a penalty. Too much coursework for a 100 level class. Rules with an iron fist, and is on a power trip.

homework every class, no late work. extremely difficult for what English 102 should be. youre dealing with a really redundant subject most people have been excessively familiar with since highschool, but he really makes you work for the grade. i got blindsided by a strange homework policy/no late work policy combination. nice guy though.

Pretty cool teacher, we got to do a lot of in class workshops and of course a lot of paper writing but he was very helpful in class and over email. If you don't mind a little homework and being involved in in group projects this is the class for you, but these really helped my paper writing.
Pretty easy going guy.  Always available and willing to help if needed.  Homework every class but allows extra credit and "do overs".  Enjoyed the class.  Learned how to write.  No final.
One of the easiest classes I've ever taken. The only assignments are posting to the discussion board about your heart rate, amount of steps you took, and where you walked.
ratingTags: EXTRA CREDIT

comment: One of the best kinesiology staff at BSU! She's a great instructor, always very helpful and open to questions. She really wants to see her students succeed.
No Comments
Best teacher I've ever had!

Denise Heald is now teaching CWID and English courses at CWI. She is often unprepared or late for class. She is sweet, but very flighty and forgetful. When doing group projects and lectures, she wasted a lot of time with out giving much content. CWID is a new course, but she was always fixing her mistakes during class. An easy A at least.

comment: Would be easy class if she wasn't as spacey and boring as she is. Asks for kind of long papers for a lower level class. Nice lady though and cares about your grade. If you can drag yourself to class everyday you'll pass.

Super nice lady, however...incredibly spacey. Easy 'A' if you can sit through the class which was the most boring class of my life. Doesn't explain things clearly at all, but does give good feedback on essays. The only reason to even go to class is you get graded on it. Other than that you could never go and still get an A. Dreaded "lectures"
Nice lady but a little out there..she often forgot homework or what the lesson plan was..but she offered quick and good feedback on essays. I liked her

comment: Professor McNamara definitely puts it all on the student. If you dont put in the work dont expect him to fix anything for you. He definitely wants his students to succeed. If you dont do ALEKS dont be surprised if you flunk out.

comment: Straightforward, normal math professor nothing out of the blue, nothing extraordinary just does his job and is there if needed.

comment: He is a nice guy but doesn't explain stuff well. You basically have to teach yourself because the Aleks system and him don't explain it well. He was a pretty good professor. You could tell during lectures that he really knew his stuff and gave great tips to make certain math processes faster. Only downside is he sometimes took forever to post our  weekly topic goals.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria--Caring

comment: His tests can be pretty hard, but he's willing to work with you. He's a nice guy and he knows what he's talking about.

Tests don't match homework very well and are exponentially more difficult. Never hands back papers but seems to be a fairly decent teacher. If he worked on his few problems he'd be a shining example of what a professor should be.

Amazing math professor.  He's a math genius AND can actually teach it to students in a way that's understandable and makes sense.  That being said, I only got one test back the entire semester.  Great, helpful prof if you want to learn the material.. not so great if you want to have any clue as to what your grade is in the class.

Very unprofessional. You will never receive a test back from him to find out how you are doing. Will not review for upcoming test, but will cover new material for the next test, just before the current test. He is very nice, but be prepared to teach and grade yourself.
He is very nice, and knows the material. Never gives grades and is quite unorganized.

He was a great teacher but very unorganized. I thought he was helpful and did a great job explaining concepts. Don't plan on having any idea though about how your doing in the class though. We took 6 tests including 2 part final. I only got one test grade back 7 weeks late.  He was also late to most classes (even the final).

i do not understand why people give him a good score. he takes forever to give back tests, you can't read his handwriting on board, he wasn't engaging at all. he was available to help if you needed it though. i don't recommend him

I'm so glad I got put into his class! Definitely the best math teacher I've ever had. I don't understand math at all and I have always hated it, he makes it tolerable and very understandable. He will explain things in as many different ways as he can think of until you understand how to solve things. Hard at some points but he's a great teacher.

Really great professor will spend extra hours making sure that you get concepts that aren't easy. The best math teacher I've ever had, easily approachable and doesn't talk down to students. If you need to take 160 take it from him.

Colin is a good teacher and really knows his math. I have two issues. The first being that he is terribly unprofessional with the timeliness of returning tests...expect to see grades from the test 3-5 weeks after taking them. Issue number 2 is that he writes so small on the board. Colin is really a good professor though and I would recommend him.

He was just an absolutely amazing teacher. He new his material well, seemed to enjoy teaching, was good at communicating to students, took time to explain, tried to challenge the students but always offered ways to make up for a bad grade. Completely recommend him.
